title: spiced nuts
directions: Cook first four ingredients until soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put on wax paper until cool and break apart.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook over medium heat until it comes to a rolling boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir and coat well.
Spread out on pan and bake for 30 minutes at 250 degrees; stir often.

title: rave reviews cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large bowl until blended.
Beat on medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove and cool completely on wire rack.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and margarine in saucepan.
Add broccoli and soup.
Put rice in casserole dish.
Add saute mixture and stir in American cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar on top.
Bake in oven at about 350° until done about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift 2 cups flour with spices.
Add alternately with milk and juice.
Mix 1 cup flour with cut up fruit.
Add beaten egg whites, then add fruit. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 325° oven.
Do not overcook.
These should be soft.
Makes about 16 dozen.

title: pecan crunchies
directions: Lightly oil a jelly roll pan and line with graham crackers. Melt butter in a medium-sized saucepan.
Add brown sugar and stir until mixture bubbles vigorously.
Add pecans and quickly spread over the graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(Check before baking time is up as these burn easily.)
Cut along indentations of the crackers.

title: orange cool whip salad
directions: Stir dry Jell-O into Cool Whip and add other drained ingredients.
Set in refrigerator.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Chop all ingredients; mix well with remaining ingredients.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix together, chill and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients and make into balls.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger meat casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Stir in tomato paste, diced cheese and macaroni.
Pour into casserole dish and bake in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza bits
directions: Spread a soda cracker with pizza sauce.
Place a piece of cheese on top of this.
Add hamburger or ham on top of cheese and sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Mix lime, orange and cherry jello separately, using 3 cups boiling water (1 cup each) and 1 1/2 cups cold water (1/2 cup each).
Put into 3 separate pans to chill until firm.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook, cool and pour over 4 or 5 sliced bananas.
Stir and top with 1/4 cup crushed peanuts.
Serve at once.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: yellow squash muffins(serves 18)
directions: Cut squash in 1-inch slices; cook in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Measure enough squash for 2 cups.
Combine squash, melted margarine and eggs; stir well and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of dry mixture and add squash mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: swiss steak with mozzarella cheese
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Coat with flour.
In large skillet with cover, melt butter.
Brown meat slowly.
Add tomatoes, salt, basil and pepper.
Cover and simmer one hour.
Add onions and green pepper and cook 30 minutes longer.
Put in serving dish.
Top meat with cheese and heat until it melts.

title: open-faced salmon patties
directions: Combine sour cream, tomato, cucumber, dill weed, salt and pepper; stir well.
Let chill.
Combine salmon, eggs, breadcrumbs, cheese, green onions, celery seed and dry mustard; mix well. Shape into 4 patties; place on a 12-inch glass plate.
Microwave at Medium-high (70% power) 5 to 6 minutes, turning once.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Top each English muffin half with lettuce and a salmon patty.
Spoon sauce over patties.
Yields 4 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip,
dry pudding mix and strawberries until well blended.
Pour into pie crust and garnish with coconut.
Chill 1 hour.
Use graham cracker pie crust.

title: potato wraps
directions: Wash potatoes and cut in fourths.
Sprinkle each with a mixture of seasonings.
Wrap one piece of bacon around each potato piece.
Sprinkle with any remaining seasonings.
Place in baking dish and bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until bacon is crispy and potatoes are done at 400°.
Drain on paper towels. Serve plain or with sour cream and chives.
Recipe can be halved.

title: strawberry upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Spoon mixture over nuts and coconut.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat. Add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in next 3 ingredients (eggs, salt and pepper). Add both cans of corn and pimento. Spoon into buttered baking dish and top with paprika. Fill metal cake pan with 1-inch of water and place casserole dish in this to bake. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand to thicken after baking.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat the eggs.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk.
Sift together and beat in 1 cup of flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat in salad oil. Add chopped apples and drop by spoonfuls in hot oil.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni. Cook shrimp; cook scallops. Layer the bottom of dish with macaroni, layer of shrimp, layer of crabmeat, layer of Mozzarella cheese, layer of macaroni, shrimp, scallops, crab and cheese.
Re-layer until dish is full and ingredients are used up.
Layer cheese on top.
Bake for 15 minutes. Ready to serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: To this mixture add cocoa mixture, mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into sheet cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.

title: three day buns(8 dozen)
directions: Mix water, 1 cup sugar and yeast; let set one day.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Melt margarine or butter and add to the Ritz crackers. Put in 9 x 13 pan and pat down.

title: perfect cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast, salt, vanilla and warm water together. Add flour, a little bit at a time.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl to rise for 1 hour.
Punch down; roll out flat. Brush on melted margarine.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over margarine.
Roll and cut.
Place on greased pans to rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot cranberry bake
directions: Layer apples and cranberries in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice and spoon sugar over fruit. Set aside.
Combine oats, pecans, brown sugar and butter.
Stir until ingredients are moistened and mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm, topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Add all ingredients; cook over medium heat until peanuts become light brown.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in a teaspoon baking soda and spread thinly on greased shallow pan.

title: brown sugar and cinnamon pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add 3/4 cup milk and the eggs to the flour mixture.
Mix well.
Then beat one minute.
Add remaining milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan or Bundt pan at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove from pan to cake rack.
When cool, spoon on Glaze.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookies, then put on round pizza pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled crust.

title: e-z chili
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes.
Let simmer until ready to serve.
If you would like hotter chili use medium or hot salsa.
Serve with French rolls.

title: caramel corn
directions: A good many husbands are very spoiled by mismanagement in cooking and so they're not very tender and good.
Some women keep them constantly in hot water, others freeze them, others put them in a stew, others roast them and others keep them constantly in a pickle.

title: whipped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water with 1/2 teaspoon salt until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Beat potatoes with 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper, milk and butter until fluffy.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Combine Oreos and the melted butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1/3 cup crumbs for top. Mix at high speed the cream cheese, pudding mix, powdered sugar and the milk until thickened. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spread over Oreo crust and refrigerate. (Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.)

title: ravioli with summer squash
directions: Cook ravioli to desired doneness as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with hot water; set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium high heat until hot.
Add zucchini, yellow squash, bell pepper, onions and garlic.
Cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Cook an additional 3 to 5 minutes, or until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain fruit juice.
Heat and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Let cool. Add Coke.
Let set in refrigerator.
Stir in nuts, cheese and fruit.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: sweet 'n' sour stew beef
directions: Brown beef in oil; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except the cornstarch and the tablespoon of water.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lacy oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt oleo or butter until it bubbles.
Add sugar and stir well. Add remaining ingredients.
Form small ball of batter (1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon) and drop on greased foil on a cookie sheet.
Flatten with back of spoon.
Bake until light golden brown in oven preheated to 325° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Peel off foil when completely cooled.

title: baked peach pudding
directions: Place sliced peaches in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Add baking powder, flour and milk. Spread over peaches.
Mix 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt. Sprinkle mixture over batter in pan.
Pour boiling water over all and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies and pour melted butter over crumbs. Stir and mash into large pan or dish. Chill while doing next step. Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 Cool Whip until smooth. Spread over cookie crust. Chill. Mix pudding and spread over last layer. Spread the second Cool Whip over pudding. Chill for several hours.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar; beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour batter into greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake is done.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make roux out of flour and cooking oil over low to medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is brown.
Add onions, celery, pepper and garlic; cook until soft.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and tomato puree, mix well and cook about 5 minutes.
Add 6 cups water and Cajun herb.
Mix to taste.
Let simmer for one hour.
Add raw shrimp, cook for 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add salt, parsley and onion tops.
Adjust seasonings as needed. Serve over rice.
Serves 10.

title: huevos rancheros(mexican ranch eggs)
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients in a frying pan and simmer to blend flavors.
Poach eggs in sauce (cover eggs as they cook).
Top with cheese 1 minute before cooked.
Serve egg and sauce on a warm tortilla.
Also serve:
pinto beans; rice or grits, tomatoes, avocados and warm buttered tortillas.

title: stir-fried rice
directions: Toss the rice, soy sauce, eggs and onions with any of the remaining ingredients in any amount or combination or anything else that tickles your fancy; be creative!
Heat until warm. Carries well to outings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Mix thoroughly. Add apples. Bake in greased pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: southern sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Place in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour; add broth.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in sherry, salt and nutmeg; keep warm. Bone and slice chicken breasts.
Blend mayonnaise and 1/2 cup cheese into sauce.
Pour half over broccoli.
Top with chicken. Blend cream into remaining sauce; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 20 minutes).
Then broil until golden.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Brush on meats, turning frequently during last 20 minutes of grilling.
Makes about 1 1/2 c. sauce.

title: spicy walnuts
directions: Heat walnut halves in moderate oven (375°) for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In saucepan, combine sugar, water, cinnamon and salt.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling.
Cook, without stirring, to soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat.
Beat, by hand, 1 minute or until mixture just begins to get creamy.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and the warm walnuts.
Stir gently until nuts are well coated and mixture becomes creamy.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together; let stand 2 hours to overnight.
Drain well before serving.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Cook meat, onions and peppers together until done.
Drain grease off of meat, then add vegetables and bouillon cube.
Add cornstarch or flour to thicken if necessary.
Salt and pepper to season.

title: anne's eggplant and pasta
directions: Peel eggplant,
slice
into
pieces and salt.
Place in colander to
drain for 30 minutes.
Saute garlic in olive oil. Do not
brown
garlic.
Add parsley, tomatoes, hot peppers and basil. Cook uncovered 25 minutes.

title: play dough(non-edible)
directions: Pour the flour and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Stir well with a spoon.
Pour the water into the bowl and mix with your fingers.
Add the oil and continue mixing with your fingers until thoroughly mixed.
Your clay should be ready to use.
To keep clay fresh, place in a plastic bag and tie tightly.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until firm.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water until dissolved, then mix other ingredients.
Let rise in a greased bowl until double.
Punch down; make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Brush tops with butter and bake at 375° until lightly brown.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Add Jell-O, strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in bowl.
Refrigerate. Leave other 1/2 out so it doesn't set.
When refrigerated mixture is set, spread on sour cream and carefully pour on unset Jell-O. Refrigerate until set.

title: tortellini with broccoli and mushrooms
directions: Cook tortellini to desired doneness.
Drain; keep warm. Meanwhile, in large skillet, combine chicken broth and 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add broccoli.
Cook over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender, stirring frequently. Stir in mushrooms, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook 4 to 6 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Stir in tortellini and remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Cook an additional 2 to 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring frequently.
Makes
5 (1 cup) servings.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork chops on both sides.
Place onions on top.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over onions and chops.
Cook on top of stove on low for 55 to 60 minutes, covered.
Spoon sauce over occasionally.

title: banana breakfast shake
directions: Place all ingredients into blender.
Blend on high speed for 45 seconds or until creamy and smooth.
Serve in a tall glass.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Boil chicken and remove meat from bones. Save water for later. Saute sausage, onion and bell pepper
in cooking oil. Add chicken and season with salt and pepper. Add 7 cups water, using water chicken was boiled in.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add Kitchen Bouquet.
Add the jambalaya mix and rice.
Stir until mixed.
Heat on low.
Cook in covered pot about 30 minutes or until rice is done.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Take from freezer early to cut.
Do not put in Tupperware!

title: aunt fearl's cracker jacks
directions: Boil together margarine, sugar, syrup and molasses for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add soda.
Stir for a few minutes. Pour over popcorn and peanuts.
Coat real good.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Let cool, then eat.

title: magic bars
directions: Melt margarine or butter. Sprinkle grahams in butter/margarine and press into buttered 8 x 8 pan. Layer coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and nuts over crust in order listed. Dribble condensed milk over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (If glass pan is used, bake at 325°.) Watch closely so Magic Bars don't get too brown. When bars are done, condensed milk will appear yellow and chips should be slightly melted. Store at room temperature in airtight container.

title: strawberry-graham shortcake
directions: Cream together the butter, brown sugar and vanilla in a bowl until fluffy; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; combine with walnuts and graham cracker crumbs.
Add to egg mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Spread batter in two greased wax paper-lined 9-inch square cake pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cakes test done.
Cool slightly; remove from pans.
Whip cream with sugar and orange extract until soft peaks form.
Spread on cold cake layers.
Slice 1 pint strawberries over 1 cake; top with second cake.
Garnish with whole berries.
Yield: one (9-inch) square cake.

title: turkey and stuffing pie
directions: Press stuffing onto the bottom and up the sides of a well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Top with turkey and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.	Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: baked ham slice-sauterne
directions: Place ham in a shallow baking pan. Mix sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan. Stir in water and butter. Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in raisins and wine. Pour over ham and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: delicious pancakes
directions: Beat eggs slightly; sift dry ingredients. Add margarine and milk to eggs. Add dry ingredients. Beat only until all flour is mixed. Batter should be lumpy; do not overmix. Bake on hot griddle.

title: hot reuben appetizer
directions: Mix together ingredients for dip.
Hollow out loaf of round rye bread.
Fill it with creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with rye bread chunks, crackers or other bread of your choice.

title: golden easter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir sugar, oil and salt into yeast mixture.
Add eggs, lemon rind and 2 cups flour; beat at low speed with an electric mixer until mixture is smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface.
Add raisins; knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover; let rise in warm place (85°) free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put pecans in jelly roll pan.
Roast 30 minutes, stirring once.
Remove from oven.
Pour melted butter over pecans.
Stir with wooden spoon to coat.
Return to oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir 2 to 3 times.
Remove from oven; add salt. Stir to coat nuts.
Roast 5 to 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Rinse and clean beans. Soak beans overnight or at least 8 hours in cold water with the salt.
Drain and add water.
Fry bacon and salt pork with onions; drain. Add to beans along with potatoes, paprika and saffron.
Add ham. Cook until potatoes are done.
Add sausage.
Keep warm and serve with crusty Cuban bread or Cuban sandwiches.

title: cold vegetable casserole
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients in water until noodles are done. Drain water.
While noodles are boiling, in a large bowl, put rest of ingredients.
When noodles are drained, add in bowl.
Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Lay chicken pieces into soup and rice mixture. Salt and pepper to taste. Top with margarine pieces. Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 400°. Remove foil for the last 30 minutes of baking time.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water, vinegar and seasonings.
Chop, cut or grate any combination of fresh vegetables.
Add to jello mixture plus olives.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce with salad dressing.

title: scalded corn cakes
directions: Add salt to boiling water.
Gradually mix in meal.
Set in refrigerator for about 20 minutes (or until chilled and firm).
In 1 inch of shortening in a skillet fry at 350° for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 18 corn cakes.

title: minutemen macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon, 1-inch apart onto well-greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove at once from sheet.
Makes 30.

title: chicken with cranberry sauce
directions: Spray a glass 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
In a bowl, mix together whole cranberry sauce, French dressing and dry onion mix. Place chicken breasts in glass dish and cover with sauce.
Be sure all chicken is covered with sauce.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
If sauce is leftover, you can freeze to be used next time.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Drain and mix fruit together.
Prepare pudding by directions on package.
In punch bowl, layer angel food cake (broken in pieces), vanilla pudding, fruit and Cool Whip.
Make 3 to 4 layers, ending with Cool Whip.
If you don't have a punch bowl, half the recipe and use glass bowl.

title: carolina chocolate delight
directions: Combine margarine, milk, cocoa and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla and mix.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper or pour all into 8 x 10-inch cake pan to form squares.
Place in refrigerator to cool.

title: italian cannoli
directions: In a small bowl, mix eggs with wine; set aside.
Blend into flour the Crisco and crumble with hands until it forms small crumbly balls; make a well and add egg mixture.
Blend flour and knead.
Add more wine if too stiff.
Knead well until elastic on a floured board.
Divide into small sections and roll out paper thin into 4 x 4-inch squares (depends on roller forms).

title: bridgford frozen bread
directions: Dough comes in 3-loaves in the freezer department.
Mix sugars, cinnamon and margarine together.
Pinch off balls and press raisin and sugar mixture inside until dough is used up. Sprinkle rest of mixture on top.
Let rise an hour or so. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Put all together in double boiler and beat at high speed while boiling.
Continue to beat for 7 minutes. Makes enough for a large angel food cake. Does not store well.
Use immediately
if possible.

title: pie filling
directions: For coconut cream, add 1 cup coconut to filling. Also sprinkle coconut on meringue.

title: italian sausage links in sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cook for 2 hours.
Meanwhile brown sausages to eliminate as much fat as possible.
Add to sauce.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: potato bread
directions: Whip together mashed potatoes and water.
Add yeast and honey. Let bubble slightly.
Mix in 4 cups whole wheat flour and salt. Let stand about 10 minutes.
Mix in 6 more cups whole wheat flour. Knead 10 to 12 minutes.
Let raise until double in bulk.
Divide into 3 balls.
Form into loaves, working air bubbles out by hitting the dough.
Place in 3 large Pammed loaf pans.
Let rise about 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 3 large loaves.

title: bison chili
directions: Fry burger in skillet.
In large pan, or crock pot, add burger and remaining ingredients.
Simmer for at least 1 hour. Serve in bowls or on baked potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish. Top with cheese and sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diabetic banana cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine banana, oil and vanilla.
Stir in oats, walnuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press down slightly with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: english pea and bean salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Dice celery, onion and pimentos; mix all together.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over vegetables. Chill for 24 hours.

title: farmer's casserole
directions: Grease a 2-qt. square baking dish.
Arrange potatoes evenly in the bottom of the dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, ham and green onions.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk, pepper and salt.
Pour egg mixture over potatoes in dish.
(The dish may be covered and refrigerated for several hours or overnight at this point, if you wish.)
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes (55-60 minutes if dish was put into the oven cold), or until center appears set.
Let stand 5 minutes.
6 servings.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Add Grape-Nuts; let stand.
Beat eggs, add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Combine with milk mixture.
Pour into greased dish, cover and set in a pan of hot water.
Bake in slow 300° oven until set, about 1 hour.

title: peanut crunch
directions: Cook butter, sugar,
syrup
and water in large saucepan on moderate heat until it reaches 300° or to hard crack stage. Remove from heat; quickly	stir
in nuts and spread in lightly buttered cookie sheet
pan.	Cool.
Spread
with melted chocolate (use 1/2 for
each
side)
and sprinkle with crushed nuts (1/2 cup to each side).
Cool
thoroughly
until chocolate is firm.	Remove from pan,
turn	candy over and spread remaining chocolate and nuts on other side.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Combine all ingredients and place 3/4 teaspoon in center of wonton.
Fold, wetting with a small amount of water so dough will stick.
Deep fry in hot oil for 1/2 minute on each side.
Remove and drain.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spread on tortillas (spread thickly and to edges).
Roll up tortilla.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container or wrap individually in plastic wrap.
They will keep for days.

title: green grasshopper
directions: Follow directions on Jell-O box to make Jell-O.
Add drained fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate until solid.
Cut into small squares. Add Cool
Whip and serve.
Enjoy your grasshopper.

title: hamburger corn pone pie(main dish)
directions: Brown meat and onion in melted shortening.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Pour meat mixture into a greased 1 or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cornbread batter.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: salsa pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
In a very large bowl, combine pasta with tomatoes, onions, green and red peppers, undrained chili peppers and olives; mix well.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda in large bowl. Cut in butter.
Add egg, orange peel and orange juice all at once.
Stir until moist.
Fold in raisins and cranberries.
Spoon into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
All cranberries can be used instead of raisins.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 the dressing mix for topping. Line casserole with remaining dressing mix.
Fill with squash mixture.
Cover with reserved mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine the sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook and stir until thick and clear.
Add the Jell-O; allow to cool and add 1 quart fresh strawberries.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Melt butter; dip biscuit into butter then roll in sugar, cinnamon mixture.
Place in greased round cake pan and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: natural munch'n
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan; stir in honey, lemon peel and cinnamon.
Drizzle over popcorn in a large bowl; toss gently. Add raisins, sunflower seeds and cashews.
Toss gently until well blended.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chocolate pound cake(pecan-topped)
directions: Combine butter and shortening mixing well.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and cocoa and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour batter into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over batter. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 45 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cake cool completely.

title: pickled mango
directions: Combine ingredients except mangoes.
Mix well and pour over sliced mangoes.
Mix every 2 hours.
Leave out overnight.

title: southern corn fritters
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add to melted butter and corn.
Beat well and drop by spoonfuls in deep fat.
When brown, serve with syrup and butter.

title: cherry salad
directions: When slightly jelled to hold fruit in place, add one can of cherry pie filling.
Stir well.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan and let set several hours.

title: lasagna d'italia
directions: Prepare the lasagna noodles.
Brown the hamburger and add to the sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes, then cool.
Mix the Mozzarella cheese and the Parmesan cheese together.

Grease pan; layer noodles, 1/3 meat sauce, 1/3 of cheese and 1/3 cottage cheese. Put 4 more noodles in the opposite direction (1/3 cheese, 1/3 meat sauce) and final 4 noodles, then meat sauce, then cheeses, ending with cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: party walnut broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until just barely tender.
Drain well and spread in an oiled 2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan.
Stir in the flour; cook briefly and then add flour.
Add the chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Set aside.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream.
Fill baked pie shell.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix
together the cheese, sugar, crab meat, garlic salt and margarine very well.
Spread on 6 English muffins.	Place on cookie
sheet,
cover
and	freeze.
When frozen, cut each muffin into
8ths.
Put
frozen
pieces
in plastic bag until needed.
To serve,
put on cookie sheet and broil for about 5 minutes.

title: hot cocktail canapes
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with the salad dressing mix. Fold in shredded cheese, pepper and meat.
This will spread 40 crackers or small bread cut outs.
Broil in oven until puffed and bubbly, about 2 minutes.
Good for parties.

title: steak supreme
directions: Heat skillet; press meat into patties to about 1/2 to 1-inch thickness.
Put in skillet.
Brown both sides.
Drain off excess fat.
Add a can of cream of mushroom soup and the same amount of water.
Cover and let simmer 20 minutes.
You cannot tell this from steak.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar, dry mustard and cornstarch.
Slowly add lemon juice, water and raisins.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Yields 2 cups.
Serve with ham or pork.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: creole green beans
directions: Cut bacon and fry; drain well.
Combine ketchup, sugar, bacon, salt and pepper, mixing thoroughly.
Pour mixture over beans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: poached salmon fillet with hollandaise
directions: Bake salmon fillet until tender and flaky.
To make Hollandaise, separate egg yolks, add cayenne pepper and lemon juice.
Whip over double boiler until "pudding like".
Remove from heat and whip butter slowly into mixture.
Whip thoroughly. Spread over salmon fillet.
Add chopped parsley for garnish.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In buttered casserole dish, layer the following: cream of mushroom sauce to cover bottom and crumbled Ritz crackers.
Lay asparagus over crackers and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in blender.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; put in a large bowl.
Dice apples and add all remaining ingredients.
Makes 12 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Soften oleo and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into pie crust and bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well except for ketchup,
then form into two loaves in baking pan. Cover with ketchup, top and sides.

title: salad surprise
directions: Early in the day, or up to one week before serving, combine vegetables in medium bowl; mix sugar, vinegar, pepper and salt; mix with the vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Serve on lettuce leaves or cup.
Decorate as desired; can also be served as a relish.

title: oven-fried mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine mustard, lemon juice, garlic, rosemary and pepper.
Coat chicken in mustard mixture.
In sealable bag, combine bran flakes and Parmesan.
Seal bag and crush bran flakes.
Place chicken pieces in a bag a few at a time and shake to coat with crumb mixture.

title: charlie's chocolate covered potato balls
directions: Mash enough brown potatoes to make a cup; stir in vanilla extract if you wish.
You can add coconut at this time, then slowly add the powdered sugar until you have the right consistency to roll into balls.
Put balls in the refrigerator while you melt chocolate.
When chocolate is ready and balls have gotten cold, you can now dip the balls in the chocolate and place them on waxed paper.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Mix together all ingredients except barbecue sauce.
Brush liberally on both sides of brisket.
Wrap in foil and "marinate" overnight in refrigerator.
Cook for 5 hours in a 300° oven, adding 6 to 8 tablespoons barbecue sauce just before the last hour.
Slice thinly and enjoy!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn broccoli
directions: Combine all ingredients (except crackers) and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover top with crackers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
This will make 2 batches, so freeze one and you are ready for the next time unexpected company arrives!

title: black forest pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and 2 tablespoons flour; add margarine and milk.
Cook until mixture begins to boil, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Add small amount of hot mixture to eggs; return mixture to pan.
Fold half can pie filling into mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until center is set but still shiny.
Cool.
Chill 1 hour. Combine 2 cups topping and grated chocolate; spread over cooled pie.
Top with remaining pie filling and topping.
Chill 1/2 hour. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: clay for play n posterity(overnight drying method)
directions: Stir in saucepan over medium heat for about 4 minutes, until the mixture thickens to moist mashed potato chip consistency. Remove from heat, turn onto plate and cover with a damp cloth until cool.
Knead as you would dough.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Warm and drain potatoes. Then mash with a fork. Add sugar, milk, cinnamon, eggs and butter. Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: taco salad
directions: Add taco seasoning to ground meat.
Mix all ingredients, except salad dressing and Doritos, together.
Just before serving, add salad dressing and Doritos.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Add all ingredients together to make soup and at the last 5 minutes of cooking add english peas. Cook for 1 hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Use a 4-quart container.
Layer lettuce, onions, celery, water chestnuts and peas.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, cheese, seasoned salt and garlic; spread over layered mixture.
Refrigerate 24 hours, covered.
Before serving, place bacon and eggs on top.
This can be tossed.

title: fresh pork sausage
directions: Mix well with meat and grind.

title: yummy granola
directions: Whiz first 5 ingredients in blender.
Add to oats, sunflower seeds, nuts and coconut.
Mix well and spread on 4 cookie sheets. Bake overnight on lowest oven setting.
Place wooden spoon or spatula in oven door to let moisture escape.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Pet milk and butter.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat ice cream, butter, brown sugar and 1/2 cup white sugar over low heat.
Cut biscuits into fourths. Roll in cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar mixture.
Fill pan.
Pour the heated mixture over all.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crusts. Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mama's homemade hush puppies
directions: Stir cornmeal into boiling water and cook until batter will form ball.
Remove from heat; stir in milk, oil and onions.
Beat eggs in a large bowl on high for 1 minute.
Gradually add cornmeal mixture to eggs while beating on low speed.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Preheat shortening.
Drop by teaspoon in shortening. Fry until golden brown.

title: nantucket scallop and cod chowder
directions: Cut bacon crosswise into 1/4-inch strips.
Heat 3 quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add bacon; saute 4 minutes or until crispy.
Remove with slotted spoon to drain on paper towel; discard fat from saucepan.

title: anna potatoes
directions: Toss potatoes in melted margarine. Generously butter shallow baking dish. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: vegetable chicken soup(yields 1 quart)
directions: Peel and cut up the tomato and add it together with the green pepper, onions and chicken to the meat broth and cook slowly until the vegetables are tender.
Other combinations of vegetables may be used and other meats also.
If you prefer, you may leave the meat out entirely and have vegetable soup.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato until smooth.
Mix in powdered sugar until it makes a ball firm enough to work.
Roll out between sheets of wax paper.
Spread peanut butter and roll up into a tight roll.
Slice in bite-size pieces.

title: garlic cheese spread
directions: Let cheeses stand until kneadable.
Add remaining ingredients. Form into 2 rolls; roll in chili powder.
Chill until firm. Great for holidays and parties.

title: frozen salad
directions: Soak bananas in reserved pineapple juice.
Mix cranberry sauce with sugar.
Add pineapple, bananas, Cool Whip and nuts (if desired).
Freeze in 2 small bread pans or 1 large bread pan.

title: jello cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar and Jell-O.
Cream well. Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to the batter a little at a time.
Mix until smooth.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Put fruit on top of batter (2 to 3 cups).
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until light brown.

title: company potatoes and boiled cabbage
directions: Combine potatoes with cream cheese, sour cream, salt and garlic salt.
Boil cabbage pieces in salt water with bacon grease until tender.
Remove cabbage from water, very carefully; drain well. Place on platter.
Spoon potatoes over cabbage.
Sprinkle on paprika.
Put 1/2 stick oleo over potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.
This freezes well.

title: spiced apple simmer
directions: In 5 quart dutch oven, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 20 minutes. Remove spices; discard.
Serve hot.

title: ooey gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together with a pastry blender the first 3 ingredients. Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat together remaining ingredients and pour over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: italian meatball soup
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Shape into 24 small meatballs.
In large saucepan, brown meatballs, then cook celery, onion and garlic until tender.
Spoon off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer on very low heat for flavors to blend (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Stir occasionally. Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening and add buttermilk all at once.
Mix well and roll out to 3/8-inch thickness and fold over.
Roll slightly again.
Cut out biscuits and bake in a 450° oven for 12 minutes.

title: vanilla butter frosting
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and vanilla. Add milk to desired consistency. Food coloring can be added to make frosting desired color.
This frosting is good to ice sugar cookies.

title: dieter's dinner salad platter
directions: Add dressing,
onions and cauliflower to drained beans. Chill about 1
hour
to blend flavors.
Put a mound of cottage cheese in the
center
of
a	serving
platter.
Arrange
half slices of tomato aspic around the cheese, with mounds of beans in lettuce nests at each end.	Yield:	6 servings.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: In a large greased casserole, toss together first 6 ingredients.
Mix together next 6 ingredients and spread over chicken mixture.
Add eggs.
Sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until heated.

title: lemon sandwiches
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice and lemon peel. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat. Add cream cheese.
Beat until smooth. Stir in pecans.
Refrigerate, covered, until well chilled.

title: green rice
directions: Cook chopped broccoli, drain and set aside.
Saute onion in oleo.
Mix all together with the broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings. Pour batter into a well greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: mamaw blanton's minute steaks and tomato gravy
directions: In a large skillet, brown minute steaks in oil.
Do not flour steaks.
When steaks are almost done, remove and set aside.
Add onion and bell pepper to oil, cooking until tender.
Remove and set aside.
Brown 1 to 2 tablespoons of flour.
Add can of tomatoes with juice.
Stir well.
Add water and cook until mixture starts to thicken.
(May need to add more water to desired consistency.)
Return steaks, onion and bell pepper back to skillet.
Stir well and simmer until steaks are thoroughly done.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Cook garlic and onions.
Add 1/2 cup water, catsup and rest of ingredients.
Heat until boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: crab salad
directions: Blend and enjoy!
Allow several hours for flavors to blend.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain grease.
Add soup, sauce and beans.
Rinse each can, leaving about 1/4 can of water in can. Add to mixture.
Add pepper (red and black), salt and chili powder to mixture.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 1 hour.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts together.
They need to be mixed very well.
You will need to use your hands.
Separate into two large sections and form into a log shape.
Sprinkle nuts over the top and onto the sides.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Serve with crackers.

title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: Combine flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and small Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Prepare milk and pudding mix according to package directions; spread over other.
Top with large Cool Whip.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 12 hours.

title: shrimp cantonese with rice
directions: Saute shrimp in margarine for 1 minute or until shrimp turns pink.
Add celery and onions.
Cook, stirring 2 minutes.
Add spinach and Chinese vegetables which have been rinsed and drained. Cover and cook 1 minute.
Blend pepper, soy sauce, chicken broth and cornstarch.
Stir into shrimp-vegetable mixture.
Cook, stirring until sauce is clear and thickened, about 2 minutes. Serve over rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: my mother's ice cream wafers
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add egg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet (about as big as a marble) and put well apart.
Top each cookie with a walnut meat in the center and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: oreo sandwiches
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted butter.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
On top of this, spoon ice cream.
Put nuts on top.
Pour chocolate sauce over this.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour, soda, cocoa, applesauce and salt; mix by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine nuts, 3 tablespoons sugar and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice, mixing until creamy.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan unroll 1 package of crescent rolls to cover pan; seal perforations. Spread cream cheese mixture over dough.
Unroll other package of rolls and seal over top of cream cheese mixture.
Mix egg whites with water and brush over pastry.
Sprinkle top with almonds and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pie shells
directions: Use pastry blender or 2 knives to cut in Crisco and flour. Add sugar and salt.
Measure water; beat in egg and add vinegar. Add to flour mixture.
Do not overmix.
Make into patties as for pie.
Makes 7 to 8 pie shells.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, margarine and oil.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well and then add all the other ingredients.
Again mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover top of batter with the chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash pumpkin seeds and place in saucepan. Cook in water and salt over low heat for 10 minutes.
Drain the seeds in a colander and lay on paper towels to dry.
In a large bowl, toss the seeds with melted butter until they are evenly coated.
Spray a cookie sheet with vegetable spray and spread the seeds over it.
Bake for 30 minutes, tossing occasionally until lightly browned.
Store in an airtight container.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel cake dessert
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding mix.
Cook over slow heat until thick.
Cool well.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into pineapple mixture.
Spread between layers of angel cake and around sides.

title: frosted apple bars
directions: Mix like pie crust. Roll out half mixture to fit a jelly roll pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into a pizza pan and bake as directed. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, garlic powder, dill weed, oregano, parsley and minced onion.
Spread mixture on crescent roll.
Put your choice of vegetables on top.
Chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and pour in one unbaked pie crust, then put other pie crust
on top of mixture.
Bake at 375°
for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil and other ingredients.
Toss with crackers.
Add Hidden Valley dressing last.
Toss again.
Keeps well in an airtight container.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: sausage rounds
directions: Brown the meat; drain it.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on party rye slices.
Freeze flat on cookie sheets, then drop into plastic bags.
Take from freezer; bake until warm.

title: cheesecake
directions: Make Jello according to directions on package.
Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: applesauce pudding
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
While cake is still hot, poke holes using a fork.
Dissolve Jell-O in water; pour over hot cake.
Put in refrigerator to cool so Jell-O can set.
Frost cool cake with whipped topping.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cover with foil or lid to bake and stir after about 15 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Cook noodles; drain water.
Brown ground beef; drain grease. Add butter.
Mash tomatoes.
Put milk in until thickened.
Add salt.
Mix all ingredients in a boiler.
Then serve.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, flour, margarine and nuts. Reserve 1/2 for topping, mix together and place in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Mix together pudding mix, milk and ice cream and pour over crust. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with 1/2 topping.

title: karithopeta(walnut cake)
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar; continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix together milk and grated orange peel. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and peel, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add nuts; mix well.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
While hot, cut into diamond shapes and pour syrup over top.
Cool 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped cream and orange wedges.
Serves 16.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
While you are mixing flour, sugar and milk together, put margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan and let melt in oven. Pour mixture in buttered pan.
Place peach slices on top of mixture.
Pour a little peach juice (1/2 can) over mixture; swirl it.
Sprinkle sugar over top with fingers.
Bake 30 minutes or until crust turns brown.

title: dirt
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar. In a separate bowl, mix the instant pudding and the milk.
Combine the two mixtures and add the Cool Whip.
Remove the white centers of the Oreos and crush the cookies.
Layer in a large flower pot, ending with the cookies.
"Plant" artificial flowers in center of pot before serving.
You may add a gummy worm coming out of the top, if you wish.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar until smooth. Gently stir in Cool Whip. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl. Add pudding mixes.
Beat 1 minute.
Stir in pumpkin and spices until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: knobby apple cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and egg together.
Add vanilla.
Mix together flour, nutmeg, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Add in the diced apples. Put in a small square pan.
This may be doubled to make a larger cake.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, small quantity at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add flour and pineapple, alternately.
Bake in a large, greased and floured tube pan at 325° to 350° (according to your oven) for 1 hour or until done.
(I cook mine at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lo-cal cabbage soup
directions: Boil bouillon and water. Add celery, cabbage, and onion salt. Then add tomato juice.

title: applesauce cream pie
directions: Beat the egg; mix with dry ingredients.
Add the applesauce and cream.
Line a pie plate with your favorite pastry.
Pour in the mixture.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) as you would a custard.

title: salisbury bourgnone
directions: Mix 1/3 cup soup, beef, crumbs, eggs and salt.
Shape into 6 oval patties.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and set aside. Brown patties in bacon drippings.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over patties.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes. Serve over noodles.
Garnish with bacon.

title: grilled skewered shrimp
directions: Roll cleaned shrimp in olive oil, then in bread crumbs with the parsley, garlic and cloves (3 cloves is not too much!).
Place shrimp on skewers (if using bamboo skewers, be sure to dampen them first).
Chill until ready to grill.
Grill quickly and enjoy. Allow about 8 shrimp per person.

title: moon cake
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil. Remove from heat. Add flour. Add eggs, one at a time, beating with wire whisk. Put in 11 x 14 pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Cool. Mix the boxes of instant pudding according to directions. Cream the cream cheese. Gradually add pudding a little at a time. Beat well to mix. Pour over pastry layer. Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Drizzle Hershey's syrup over Cool Whip.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup granulated sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter in 8 or 9-inch square baking pan (greased).
In small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup granulated sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle mixture evenly over batter.
Slowly pour hot water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Let stand 15 minutes. Spoon into desert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix cereal and raisins in a bowl; set aside.
Beat peanut butter and honey in a large bowl unti well blended.
Stir in 1 cup of the cereal mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in remaining cereal mixture.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 3 dozen balls. Store in refrigerator.

title: microwave chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart glass baking dish for 1 minute. Combine garlic, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper in large mixing dish.
Mix well.
Roll chicken in margarine; dip in crumb mixture.
Place chicken in 2-quart glass baking dish, skin side down.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes. Turn chicken pieces over.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: tuna salad(serves 1)
directions: Combine in a medium mixing bowl (do not drain tuna).
Chill and serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix thoroughly the applesauce, brown sugar and shortening; set aside.
Sift into a large bowl the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
To this flour mixture, add the raisins and pecans.
Next, add the applesauce mixture to the flour mixture. Blend well and spoon into a buttered and floured 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until done.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add to mixture rest of the ingredients.
Put in Pyrex dish.
Generously cover with bread crumbs.
Drip melted oleo over crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Sift flour; add soda and salt and sift together.
Cream shortening, add sugar gradually.
Cream all together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat.
Add cocoa and flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Frost with chocolate icing and top with a pecan half.

title: turtles
directions: (For every 10 caramels, add 1 tablespoon of margarine and 1/3 cup of pecans.)
Melt margarine in large glass bowl in microwave. Then add caramels and melt until in a liquid form in the microwave.
Add pecans and stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoons onto a buttered dish or aluminum pan.
If desired, melt a pan of chocolate chips and dip caramels to make them chocolate covered.

title: mustard sauce for seafood, etc.
directions: Beat mustard and mayonnaise together well.
Add the rest of the ingredients and beat until creamy.
Chill.
Will keep for weeks in a closed container.
Excellent.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 2 quart buttered casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees uncovered.

title: quick lunchbox cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and nuts in large bowl.
Blend at lowest speed of electric mixer.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
After final beating, stir in 1/2 bag of chocolate chips. Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle remainder of chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 305° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: yellow bean-mushroom side dish
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add mushrooms.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add yellow beans.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer slowly, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, pudding and milk together.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream.
Pour altogether.
Layer bananas and wafers.
Pour over top and put in refrigerator.

title: banana bran bread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter together in a bowl.
Beat in the eggs.
Stir in the All-Bran and mix well.
Blend in the mashed bananas, the water and the vanilla.
Stir in the chopped nuts. Sift before measuring the flour and then resift with the baking powder and soda.
Add the sifted ingredients, a little at a time, until all have been mixed into the batter.
Stir only until blended.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350° in 8 x 4-inch greased loaf pan.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs in a bowl; add brown sugar, salt, shortening and syrup.
Beat for 1 minute.
Pour into pie crust. Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes until set.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds and membrane; wash. Mix raw beef with onion, rice, salt and pepper.
Divide evenly into peppers.
Arrange peppers upright in 3-quart casserole.
Blend soup and water until smooth.
Pour over peppers.
Cover.
Microwave at High (10) for 28 to 32 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese, re-cover and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: george's vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef well in pot you will cook it in. In microwave, cook celery and carrots with some water for 10 minutes on High. Put all ingredients, except rice, in pot.
Bring to low boil, then simmer 1 1/2 hours. The last 15 to 20 minutes, add Minute rice. The main secret is browning meat well. Eat and enjoy.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain all cans except pie filling.
Mix all ingredients together in a medium/large bowl.
Ready to serve. Mixture can be chilled to serve later.
If serving later, do not add banana until ready to serve.

title: kiwi jubilee
directions: Combine apple juice and orange rind in a small skillet; bring to a boil.
Add kiwi, reduce heat and simmer until thoroughly heated.

title: hash brown potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and milk; stir in potatoes, green onion and pepper sauce.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese and half of the bacon bits.
Pour into 9-inch pie or quiche dish sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until knife in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining bacon bits and 1/2 cup cheese. Continue to bake for 3 to 4 minutes to melt cheese.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir water and mix until moistened. Drop into greased muffin pan, filling 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add salt, chili powder, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, mixed vegetables, onion and tomato soup. Then place slices of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: blue ribbon banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, mix pudding and milk; beat until pudding sets. Add sour cream; blend well.
Add Cool Whip; blend well.
Add Eagle Brand; blend well.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with vanilla wafers. Slice bananas over wafers.
Pour pudding over bananas and wafers. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: parsley tators and chops
directions: In at least 2-inch deep pan to use for broiling, place chops (your normal serving) then peel and quarter potatoes all around the chops.
Slice butter.
Put at least 1 slice on each chop, then at random on potatoes.
Pour about 1/2 cup of water in pan. Sprinkle parsley in a medium coat over all. Salt and pepper to taste. Then bake at 375° for around 45 minutes. Taters will be soft.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water; whip hot potatoes with salt, pepper, butter and milk until light and fluffy.
Pour into buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread with whipped cream and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 20 minutes (until lightly brown on top).
This recipe serves 8 to 10.

title: pat's old-fashioned teacakes
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough about size of a walnut onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press flat with the bottom of a glass that has been coated with sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: good ole dirt
directions: Cream cheese and oleo; add powdered sugar and set aside.
Mix pudding and milk until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in cream cheese mixture and set aside.
Crush Oreo cookies until fine.
Use food processor.
Set aside.

title: sour cream chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 9x13 pan.
Mix biscuit mix and water.
Pat dough into pan with dough 1/2 inch up the sides of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake about 25 minutes until edges are brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean. This is a nice luncheon dish served with a salad.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all together.
Add 1 milk can of water.
Place in 1 gallon size freezer.
Finish filling freezer with whole milk.
Freeze. May add fruit of choice.

title: play clay christmas ornaments
directions: Mix soda and cornstarch together, blending well.
Add the cold water and mix well until mixture is smooth.
Boil for 1 minute until it has consistency of moist mashed potatoes.
Stir constantly.
Spoon out on a plate.
Cover with a damp cloth; allow to cool.
Knead dough and roll out on waxed paper.
Cut out designs with a cookie cutter or shape by hand.
Let dry until hard, 1 to 2 days.
Paint ornaments with Tempra or water colors.
Dry well and coat with clear shellac.
Hangers may be mounted on back with glue or pressed into dough before it dries.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl except the crabmeat.
Then add crabmeat and fold into mixture so as not to break up the crabmeat. Make into patties and fry.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Choose a black diamond melon with thick skin. Trim outer green skin and pink flesh. Cut into cubes. (Remove all red meat.) Soak overnight in brine. Rinse and let stand in ice water 4 hours. Drain; cover with boiling water and simmer until tender (about 10 minutes).

title: pie crust
directions: Stir flour and salt.
Add oil and milk.
Mix together.
Divide mixed mixture in half.
Roll out on floured surface.
Makes a double crusted pie.

title: grandma's vegetable soup
directions: Boil ham bone in 1 quart of water for 1/2 hour or until tender. Add snap beans, peas and butter beans.
Cook until almost done. Add cabbage and let boil for 5 minutes.
Add okra and let boil for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes; let boil for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add corn. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sugar and salt to suit your taste.
Keep stirring while cooking.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Sprinkle meat with paprika.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
In large skillet or pan, brown meat in butter.
Add garlic, broth and cooking sherry.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in onion and green peppers.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook until thick.
Serve with rice and top with tomatoes.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix well, using clam juice to adjust consistency.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: salmon chowder(or corn chowder)
directions: Creamed corn may be substituted for salmon.

title: easy baked potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes with skins on into small chunks.
Put into baking pan.
Cut onions into small chunks and spread over top of potatoes.
Do butter the same way.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil and bake for 35 minutes, checking them after 15 minutes to stir so potatoes won't stick. After potatoes are done, heat Cheez Whiz and pour over potatoes.

title: turkey - creole style
directions: In saucepan cook onion, pepper, garlic and bay leaf in oleo until pepper is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except rice.
Heat.
Remove bay leaf and serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: monkey bread 1
directions: Flour and grease bottom of Bundt pan.
Cover bottom of pan with pecans.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture (coat thoroughly).
Put biscuit quarters on top of pecans. Heat butter, sugar and milk until butter melts.
Pour over biscuits and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert on plate and cool.
Pull apart to eat and enjoy!

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package (using one cup of milk) in large mixing bowl.
Whip, then beat at high speed, for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pie shell. Chill at least four hours.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and cool. Rinse and drain tuna.
Chop onions and celery.
Mix tuna, peas, pimentos, onions and celery.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Add to cooled macaroni; mix with mayonnaise.
Place in refrigerator until well chilled.
Serves 4.

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in a 1/4 c. warm water. Cream sugar and oil. Add boiling water and mix well.

Add salt, cold water, and eggs and mix. Add yeast. Add flour 2 cups at a time, beat well. Do not knead. Place in a greased container. Cover and put in a warm place and let rise till double in size, punch down.
Punch down as many times as needed until ready to make out rolls. The dough will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: power drink
directions: Place all ingredients in blender until smooth.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: smoked sausage and cabbage soup
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, cook the onion and garlic in margarine or butter until tender.
Add the water, potatoes, sausage, beans and bouillon.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered for 15 minutes.
Add the cabbage, tomato paste and vinegar.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes more.
Makes 6 main-dish servings.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse with cold water to drain well in the morning.
Add rest of ingredients to vegetables.
Mix well and cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 pints.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Dice chicken and set aside.
Cook rice in chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients together and place in a buttered 8x8-inch casserole dish.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Fry in frying pan, or bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Spread on cocktail rye.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or less.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in large salad bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar, dot over salad and spread carefully over top to sides. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese, then bacon bits, if desired.
Make night before, needs to set.

title: fruit cake #1
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake slowly for 5 hours.

title: texas caviar
directions: *I use black-eyed peas with jalapenos instead of adding jalapenos.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix pretzels, margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar.
Add next four ingredients. Beat eggs and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Spread marshmallow cream while hot.

title: marinated cabbage salad
directions: Cut head of cabbage in large bowl.
Slice onion and bell pepper in rings over cabbage.
Heat oil, vinegar, salt, celery seed, sugar and mustard.
Pour over cabbage; marinate overnight. Refrigerate; drain to serve.
Will last several days.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut each bacon slice in half and wrap around a water chestnut. Secure with toothpick and place on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with soy sauce. Broil until bacon is desired doneness.

title: pork fried rice(serves 6 to 10 people)
directions: Brown pork in frying pan with onions and garlic.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cook rice in a separate pan.
When cooked, mix rice and meat together in a large kettle. Scramble eggs in a separate frying pan.
When done, mix with rice and meat and add soy sauce to taste.
Add mushrooms.

title: crunchy freeze
directions: Melt margarine at 300° in 13 x 9-inch pan for 10 minutes. Stir in brown sugar, Rice Krispies, coconut and pecans.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Remove one-half of mixture.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Spread one-half gallon of ice cream over mixture.
Sprinkle the rest of mixture over ice cream.
Freeze at least 2 hours.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: sausage calzone bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, cook sausage and green pepper till sausage is no longer pink, drain fat.
Stir in Provolone cheese, pizza sauce and Italian seasoning.
Unroll pizza dough.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 12 inch square. Cut into 16 - 3 inch squares.
Spoon teaspoonful of sausage mixture onto half of each square. Moisten edges of dough with water and fold over, forming a triangle.
Press edges with fork to seal.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Prick tops of calzone with fork, brush lightly with milk and sprinkle Romano cheese.
Bake 12-15 minutes or till brown.
Warm remaining pizza sauce for dipping.
Makes 16 mini calzone.

title: grandma gibson's easy baked beans
directions: Mix pork and beans, Karo syrup and ketchup in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until beans are firm, but not dry, and bacon is well browned.

title: dieter's dream?
directions: Crumble together the flour, pecans and butter.
Press into an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; cool.

title: chili and cheese, ole!
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly.
In another skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and saute until just tender.
Add tomato sauce, chili seasoning mix and water.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add cream and mix well.
Remove tomato mixture from heat.
Add egg-cream mixture slowly, stirring constantly.
Place half of the corn chips in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Top with half of the browned beef.
Cover with a layer of half the Monterey Jack cheese, then add layer of tomato sauce.
Repeat the layers.
Top with the sour cream and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
I do all the preparation ahead of time and then assemble at the last minute!

title: mexican hot hominy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in crock-pot for 6 hours on high.
When ready to serve, sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top while hot.

title: apple delight
directions: Beat ingredients together until light and fluffy.
Stir in:

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix everything together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on baking sheet.

title: fried apples
directions: Wash, quarter and core apples; don't peel. Melt butter in skillet; add apples and add lots of brown sugar and a little water. Cook slow until tender and candied.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, Jell-O,
milk,
oil
and
eggs
until smooth.
Mix the coconut, strawberries
and nuts in a separate bowl.
Mix half of this into the
cake batter.
Save the other half for icing.
Bake in 3 layers at
350°	for
25 to 30 minutes. Into the last half
of
coconut
mixture,	add powdered sugar and margarine for icing.

title: three layered chocolate dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Cool and crumble 1/2 of cake in large glass bowl.
On top of cake put 1/2 of the prepared pudding, then 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Crumble 3 of the Heath bars and sprinkle on top.
Repeat with second layer.
Finish with Heath bars.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet and crumble into small pieces and set aside.
In the same skillet, pour in oil, flour, salt and pepper.
Heat on medium-high heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add milk and stir until thick.
If too thick, add more milk.

title: mom's date bars
directions: Combine and cook first 3 ingredients over moderate heat until slightly thick.
Combine and blend remaining ingredients.
Press half of mixture into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread with date mixture; and cover with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: biscuits (self-rising)
directions: In large bowl, cut shortening into flour; add milk.
Stir with fork to form soft dough.
One to three tablespoons additional milk may be added to achieve desired consistency.
Turn onto floured surface; gently knead.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch floured cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat the oil in a skillet.
Saute the onions and celery for a few minutes.
Add rice; stir to separate kernels.
Add the meat and vegetables.
Cook, stirring just enough to heat through. Sprinkle with soy sauce, if desired.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: fruit crush punch
directions: Combine citric acid and boiling water in a ceramic heatproof container; stir until citric acid dissolves.
Let mixture stand 24 hours.
Combine sugar and 5 quarts cold water; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add citric acid mixture, chilled pineapple juice and orange juice concentrate; stir mixture.
Serve over ice.
Yield: 8 1/2 quarts.

title: cio clare
directions: In large skillet or saucepan, heat oil and butter.
Add onion and garlic.
Allow to melt and turn translucent.
Add the Prosciutto; saute gently 2 minutes.
Add chopped tomatoes and cook 5 minutes or until oil separates from vegetables.
Add beef and chicken stock, chopped parsley and peas.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add whipping cream.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons flour mixed with water to form a paste.
Serve over linguine.
Add 1/3 to 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese while mixing.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the black-eyes peas, green pepper, celery and both onions.
In a small bowl, combine the oil, sugar, vinegar, garlic, salt, black pepper and hot sauce.
Pour the dressing over the beans.
Toss.
Let stand overnight for the flavors to meld.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Pour boiling water over; let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Add sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add flour paste to thicken. Remove from fire; cool.
Add salad dressing.
Put into pint jars and seal.

title: chili casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain the grease.
Mix all ingredients (except the cheese) together in casserole dish or baking pan. Stir in 8 ounces of shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top with 8 ounces shredded cheese about 10 minutes before done.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese in a small bowl. Add peppermint extract.
Divide mixture in half.
Add red food coloring to one half and green food coloring to other.
Knead until consistency of pie dough.
Form dough into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Press into candy molds.
Remove immediately. Yield:
about 2 dozen mints.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix and freeze until slushy.
Stir several times while freezing to mix the strawberries.
Serve slushy.
If made ahead, may be frozen then defrosted to slushy.

title: shrimp pasta sauce
directions: Saute garlic and oregano in oil.
Add shrimp and saute until done; add sauce and wine.
Serve.

title: oatmeal raisin walnut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Combine the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add oats and raisins.
Mix well.
Add walnuts.
Mix well.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: great american potato salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt, dill weed and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly and refrigerate.

title: fudge chocolate pie
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine.
Gradually add sugar and beat with mixer.
