Add cocoa.
Gradually add milk, while beating.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt; beat again.
If you have a blender, put all ingredients in the blender and blend until smooth.
Pour into unbaked crust.
(Don't forget to prick pie shell.)
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and then refrigerate for several hours.

title: raspberry-filled cookies
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter together until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Blend well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
When chilled, shape into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press down centers with thumb and sprinkle with green sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
If still too high, press middle down with spoon halfway through baking.
Cool and fill with jam just before serving. Makes 4 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; bake with lid on at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spoon into a 12-cup muffin pan that has been greased or sprayed with nonstick spray. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat down in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Coat top with ketchup.
Sprinkle 1/2 to 3/4 cup brown sugar on top.
Cook in microwave for 10 minutes.
Turn 1/2 turn and cook 10 more minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients into saucepan; add milk, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until thick and smooth. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: tomato jam
directions: Scald, peel and chop tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Measure fruit in saucepan; add the exact amount of sugar and mix well.
Place over high heat, bring to full rolling boil and boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; at once stir in Certo.
Skim off foam with metal spoon, then stir and skim for 5 minutes to cool slightly, to prevent floating fruit. Ladle into glasses; cover at once with 1/8 inch hot paraffin. Makes 9 medium glasses.
(If you like strawberry jam, you will like this.)

title: potato chip potatoes
directions: In a bowl, combine the potatoes, 1/2 cup of potato chips, onion, butter, salt and pepper; toss to combine.
Transfer to a greased shallow 2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining potato chips.
Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy strawberry-lemon squares
directions: Mix graham crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter until blended. Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: colorful molded lollipops
directions: Brush inside surfaces of lollipop molds with oil.
Combine sugar, syrup and water in a medium saucepan; stir well.
Cook over low heat without stirring until candy thermometer reaches hard crack stage (310°).
Remove from heat; stir in peppermint extract and food coloring.
Immediately pour hot mixture into molds. Press sticks in indentations of molds, gently twirling to embed. Cool completely; lift lollipops out of molds and wrap tightly in plastic wrap.
Store in a cool dry place.
Yield:
About 8 (2-inch) lollipops.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Mix and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, cream cheese, garlic powder, lemon juice, wis sauce and onion.
Shape into ball or balls and roll in paprika and parsley.

title: pan broiled liver slices with soy sauce(servings:  8)
directions: Slice the liver thin and drain well after soaking it for 20 minutes.
Mince green onion, garlic, ginger and red pepper. Combine seasonings for them.
Marinate the above together for 30 minutes.
Pan broil over medium heat on both sides.
Place lettuce leaves on the plate and boiled liver in the center of it.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and section orange; cut in small pieces.
Combine fruits, celery and nuts.
Mix mayonnaise and cream.
Fold in fruit.
Turn in shallow refrigerator freezing tray and freeze, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: fall apple dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients except last two.
Wash and slice apples and dip in orange juice.
Arrange in circles on a plate and place dip in center.
Sprinkle additional chopped nuts on top of dip.

title: potato toss
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill in refrigerator to mix flavors.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.

title: lite fruit pie
directions: Prepare pudding as directed and pour into pie crusts.
Slice bananas into bowl and cover surfaces with lemon juice.
Arrange a layer of banana slices over pudding.
Fold 3/4 cup chopped pecans into Cool Whip and spread over bananas.
Arrange mandarin slices and chopped cherries or strawberries on top of Cool Whip. Sprinkle 1/4 cup pecans over top.
Refrigerate at least two hours.

title: cole slaw dressing(for 3 pounds cabbage)
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil and pour over cabbage, onions and peppers.

title: venison steak
directions: Salt and pepper steaks and cut into serving pieces.
Flour lightly and brown in oil.
Drain off excess oil.
Layer meat, green pepper, onions and mushrooms in skillet or baking dish. Cover with gravy and wine.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 or 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: sweetheart pie
directions: Measure the water into 4-cup liquid measure.
Stir in gelatin. Microwave on High for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add ice cream to hot mixture 1 spoonful at a time, stirring until cream is melted. Chill for 30 minutes, stirring twice (mixture should mound when dropped from spoon).
Pour chilled ice cream mixture into pie shell; chill about 4 hours or until ice cream mixture does not jiggle if tilted slightly.
Decorate with chocolate sprinkles or grated chocolate.
Garnish with whipped topping before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: icebox cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together, except graham crackers.
Roll graham crackers fine.
Put 1/2 in bottom of mold; pour jello mixture in.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 graham cracker mixture over the top.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: rhubarb crunch cake
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter and brown sugar; blend in eggs and vanilla.
Dissolve soda in sour cream.
Stir in alternately with flour.
Add nuts and rhubarb.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May be served warm with cream.

title: mamaw's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg and beat well.
Add flour, which has been sifted with baking powder, alternately with milk and vanilla.
Chill well.
Roll thin and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Slowly cook spinach in a very small amount of water.
Do not drain liquid.
Cool slightly.
Fold in sour cream and onion soup mix.
Pour into greased casserole, sprayed with Pam.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bacon.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper. Cook until meat is brown and vegetables are tender, then drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes. Serve on buns.

title: calico salad
directions: Mix the vinegar, oil, sugar and pepper and bring to a boil. Pour hot mixture over drained peas, corn, pimentos and green onions.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix with other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Sweeten blueberries with some of the sugar; set aside.

title: three bean barbecue
directions: Crumble and fry hamburg; drain.
Crisp-fry bacon (cut in chunks or pieces).
Saute chopped onion in bacon fat.
Drain.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix together.
Cook in your crock-pot on high for 1 hour or low for 3 hours.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese and 1/2 cup crumbs.
Pour into shallow casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: greens loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Fry celery leaves in butter over low heat until wilted.
Sprinkle with flour and blend well.
Add greens, cooking greens juice and beaten egg.
Stir over low heat until warm.
Pour into mixing bowl with rice, salt and celery seed; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and place bacon strips on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until firm and lightly browned.
Unmold and serve hot.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Spread cheese evenly in bottom of the pie shell and pour the milk mixture over it.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg and dot with margarine. Place pie on a cookie sheet. Bake for 30 minutes or until set.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain kidney and lima beans, saving the liquid.
In a pan, brown the bacon, ground beef and onion.
Combine all ingredients. Pour into greased, 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: no peeking stew
directions: Add all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook for 6 hours on high.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Melt butter in skillet. Saut celery and onions until tender. Tear up cornbread and bread into small pieces. In large mixing bowl, combine cornbread, bread, cooked celery and onions, sage and pepper. Stir broth and eggs into mixture. Blend well. Pour in baking dish and bake in a preheated 450° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend together cracker crumbs and peanut butter.
Add sugar substitute and baking powder.
Add egg yolks and milk; mix well. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
8 cookies.
Carbohydrate 9.2 g, protein 2.5 g, fat 4.6 g, calories 88.
One cookie = 1/2 bread exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and chop broccoli.
Brown bacon and crumble.
Add chopped onion and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients to make a dressing.
Add dressing to broccoli.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle meat with meat tenderizer according to package directions.
Slice meat across the grain into 1/2-inch wide strips.
In a large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Add meat and cook over high heat until browned on all sides.
Remove from pan.
Add remaining butter to skillet.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, ketchup and salt and pepper to taste. Gradually add broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in dill weed, mushroom soup and sour cream.
Add mushrooms and beef; cook, stirring constantly, until heated through.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: tropical cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and allspice in bowl.
Add butter, molasses and bananas and mix 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
You can sprinkle sugar on top of cake before baking for a crisp topping or ice after baking.

title: grape juice pie
directions: Heat juice and water.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir in sugar and flour; add to juice.
Cook until thick.
Cool and pour into baked crust.
Top with meringue made from the egg whites.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add oil, vinegar, vanilla and 2 cups cold water.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325°
for 40 minutes, or until done.

title: dimitri's bitkis(russian meat balls)
directions: Crumble crackers into milk; let stand until soft.
Saute onion until golden brown.
Beat eggs lightly with a fork and add to crackers; add salt and pepper.
Combine onion and cracker mixture with ground meat and mix well.
Shape into small balls; roll in flour and brown in hot butter.
Drain pan drippings; add 1 cup of beef stock and remaining flour and bring slowly to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add horseradish before removing from heat. Place meat balls in casserole, pour sauce over and cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixing bowl, blend Crisco, sugar, vanilla and orange peel.
Blend in eggs.
Combine the flour, baking powder, salt and mace; add alternately with the milk to the shortening-sugar mixture.
Beat well.

title: scallops and mushrooms
directions: Parboil scallops.
Drain and cut into small pieces.
Reserve 1 cup scallop liquid.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter 10 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Add 1 cup scallop liquid and cream gradually.
Stir until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Add scallops and season.
Pour into buttered baking dish or scallop shells.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bits of butter. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: african dish
directions: Boil chicken and seasonings.
Cook until about half done.
Add corn, whole tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook until meat is done. Add cabbage; cook for about 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter; mix with sugar.
Cool a little.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: 7 layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order given in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over all.
Sprinkle sugar over this.
Add bacon chips and cheese.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade soup with egg noodles
directions: Combine egg, milk and salt.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough (about 1 cup).
Roll very thin on floured surface; let stand 20 minutes.
Slice 1/4-inch strips; let dry about 2 hours.
Drop into boiling soup and cook uncovered about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 cups cooked noodles.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion, salt and 2 cups water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain; do not rinse.
Pack into containers.
Mix sugar and vinegar and pour over cucumbers.
Freeze.
Do not heat vinegar.

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Pour milk, soda, peaches and sugar into blender and blend. Beat eggs and mix with rest of ingredients.
Pour in ice cream bucket and freeze.

title: barbecued shrimp(serving size: 2)
directions: Wash shrimp thoroughly and place in a very large shallow pan. Add celery and garlic.
Squeeze juice from 2 lemons over top.
Dot shrimp with butter and sprinkle with remaining ingredients, except lemon wedges.
Place shrimp under broiler until butter melts and shrimp start to turn pink (about 5 minutes), stirring several times.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chippers
directions: Place oats in food processor bowl or container of electric blender; process until finely ground.
Set aside.
Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add whole egg and vanilla, beating well.
Combine ground oats, flour and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Stir in chocolate morsels.
Drop dough by tablespoon onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: b.l.t. dip
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces (I found the easiest way is to cut with scissors).
Cook bacon until crispy.
Drain fat grease.
Cut tomato into small pieces; remove seeds.
In a small bowl or small shallow casserole dish, combine first 4 ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Cut in finger-size bits.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into prepared graham cracker crust (or chocolate).
Chill.
Garnish with shaved chocolate pieces.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine and chill for 2 hours.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in flat pan.
Cover with 1 can tomato soup that is thinned down with juice from peas.
Bake a couple of hours, or until done.
One-half hour before serving, pour on drained peas.
Serve with baked potatoes.

title: people chow
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips together.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add cereal and mix well. Add powdered sugar and mix. Serve in clean dog food bowl for fun!

title: creamy cake frosting
directions: Combine milk and flour in saucepan and cook until thickened (bubbling).
Place in refrigerator to cool for about 10 minutes. In a bowl, mix sugar, oleo, shortening and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add the thickened milk and flour mixture.
Beat until very smooth.
Makes an excellent frosting.
It can also be used as a filling for Whoopie Pies.

title: brown rice
directions: Place in order given in 1-quart casserole.
Cook 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: bacon and cheddar chicken
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp, then drain and crumble.
Discard all but 3 tablespoons drippings from skillet. Reserve skillet and bacon.
Dip chicken first into the egg, then into bread crumbs to coat completely.
Saute in hot bacon drippings for 4 to 5 minutes over medium high heat until brown on both sides. When chicken is nearly cooked, top with shredded cheese.
Cover about 30 seconds to melt cheese, then remove from skillet.
Serve garnished with crumbled bacon.

title: party potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes with electric mixer until smooth.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
If mixture is too stiff, add milk.
Place in buttered 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
24 servings. Garnish with a large sprig of parsley.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's blueberry cream pie
directions: In condensed milk, add lemon juice and mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Top with blueberry filling.
You can also use pineapple with 1/2 cup coconut.
Top with nuts.
Chill pie.

title: chocolate coconut macaroons
directions: Melt the chocolate; stir in the sugar, coconut, vanilla and cream.
Let cool completely.
Beat the egg whites with salt until stiff.
Add the chocolate mixture; fold together gently but thoroughly with a metal spoon.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets lined with parchment, leaving room for spreading. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until firm to the touch.
Let cool on the cookie sheets.

title: mini mushroom meat loaves
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushroom soup.
Shape into patties.
Brown both sides of patties in iron skillet.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Simmer 15 minutes or until meat is cooked to desired doneness.
Delicious served with rice or boiled potatoes. Use mushroom soup sauce as gravy.

title: ham-vegetable casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in 1/4 cup oleo until tender, not brown.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add tomatoes and milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in ham and vegetables.
Turn into 13 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients. Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and stir into first mixture. Chill dough and roll into balls the size of walnuts. Roll in a cinnamon and sugar mixture. Bake about 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until light brown, but still soft. They will spread while baking into round cookies, crackled on top. Yield: 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add cream.
Mix salt, sugar and flour together.
Add to egg mixture and pour over rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: In large pot, combine bouillon cubes, water, celery, onions and cook for 20 minutes.
Next, add potatoes, carrots, and mixed vegetables and cook for another 30 minutes.
Next, add cream of chicken soup, 1/2 can of water, evaporated milk, and velveeta cheese.
Bring to a slow boil.
Turn heat down and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix flour, 2 1/2 cups sugar, oil, eggs, salt, orange juice, vanilla and baking powder.
Set aside.
Fold apples with 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Alternate batter and apples.
(Start with batter, end with apples.)
Bake approximately 2 hours at 350°.
Place shallow pan full of water below cake rack to keep cake moist.

title: easy lime cake
directions: Mix by hand the limeade, milk and sour cream with food coloring.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust. Chill.
Garnish with shaved chocolate, if desired.
Based on 8 servings, this contains 435 calories, 23 g fat, 219 mg sodium and 26 mg cholesterol per serving.

title: italian dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: In greased 3-quart casserole or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer potatoes, corn, onion and carrots.
Season each layer with salt. Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to the ground beef.
Pour this over your casserole on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.
You can use other vegetables if you wish. Serves 6.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spread on muffin halves and freeze on cookie sheet.
Cut in eighths and return to freezer or bake.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°, then broil a couple of minutes. Delicious.

title: barbecue sauce for turkey
directions: Cut turkey in 3-inch strips.
Soak 8 to 10 hours.
Cook 30 minutes and turn often.
Baste with sauce each time you turn.

title: baked yellow squash
directions: Clean squash and cut into 1 in slices.
Place in a sauce pan and cover with water.
Cook squash until tender.
Drain off the water and add margarine and onion, egg, salt, pepper and sugar plus cornbread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegetable beef casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
In large bowl, add ground beef, onion and vegetable beef soup.
Boil macaroni; drain and add to rest of ingredients.
Add cheese, slice by slice.
Mix in 1/2 to 1 can of water; stir until mixture is creamy.
Bake for 15 to 30 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: snowman snack
directions: Spread icing on the ground (graham cracker).
Glue marshmallows together with icing.
Place marshmallow snowman on the ground. Glue chocolate chips for eyes with icing.
Sprinkle with snow (coconut).
Yummy!

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese until Jell-O melts.
Add drained pineapple and oranges.
Add marshmallows and fold in Cool Whip.

title: red rice
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients into a 2-quart pan.
Add hot water and bring to a boil.
Stir often.
Cook 20 minutes, uncovered, until water is gone and rice is tender.
If not, add more water and cook until tender.

title: ma's german apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening. Mix will resemble cornmeal.
Use within 10 to 12 weeks.
Makes about seven cups.

title: sarah's sausage casserole
directions: Add sausage to egg mixture.
Butter dish.
Trim bread.
In buttered pan, put a layer of bread.
Top with sausage mixture, then another layer of bread topped with sausage mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until set.
This can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: anita's angel food strawberry cake
directions: Boil 2 cups of water.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
In a separate bowl, whip 2 packages of whipping cream.
When strawberries are broken up, fold whipped cream into strawberry mixture.
Pour mixture in angel food pan. Break cake into large pieces.
Put a layer of cake and strawberry mixture over it.
Then more cake again with mixture over it.
You end up with strawberry mixture on top.
Take last package of whipping cream, add a little sugar and frost cake.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook ground beef and next 3 ingredients in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring, until meat browns and crumbles. Drain well; set aside.

title: ham, potato, pea scallop
directions: In microwave, saute onions in butter (1 1/2 minutes raw, 1/2 minute dried).
Blend flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook 4 1/2 minutes; stir every 1/2 minute.
Combine potatoes, peas and ham. Place cheese slices on top.
Cook 5 minutes.
Turn dish halfway through cooking time.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: coon or possum and pecans
directions: Skin possum. Remove glands and entrails.
Scrape clean and scald in boiling water. Rub inside and out with salt and pepper. Set in a cool place.
Stuff with pecans, applesauce and bread crumbs.
Cover with lemon juice, slices of sweet taters and cane syrup. Add 1 cup of water to pan. Bake at 325°, basting often, until tender. Add liquid, if needed.
Serve with rice and mustard greens.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sauerkraut, onion, carrots, green pepper and pimento in a large bowl.
Mix vinegar, oil and sugar in small bowl.
Stir vigorously.
Pour over sauerkraut mixture, stirring to coat. Chill overnight.

title: fresh spinach and mushroom salad
directions: In a small bowl or jar, combine garlic, salt, thyme, oil and vinegar.
Shake and pour over salad.

title: chicken velvet
directions: If using chicken breasts, cut the partially frozen meat into strips.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in 2 tablespoons Crisco; then pour off grease.
Stir in soup, water or broth, thyme and tarragon.
Add carrots; cover and simmer over low heat for about 15 minutes.
Add potatoes and continue to cook for 30 minutes.

title: lemonade
directions: Into a 1-quart can with tight fitting lid, put sugar and lemon peel.
Add 1 1/2 cups very hot water.
With lid fitted tightly, shake jar until sugar is dissolved; add lemon juice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli	for
5	minutes.
In baking dish, layer broccoli, water
chestnuts,
onion and cheese.
Repeat layers. Spread soup over
all.
Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes (or until bubbly).

title: busy day casserole
directions: Line greased casserole with seasoned meat and add chopped onion and sliced potatoes over this. Pour diluted soup over this and cook until potatoes are done in 350° oven. Add cheese over top and let melt.

title: two-potato soup
directions: Combine onion, water and garlic in Dutch oven.
Cover; cook over low heat until water evaporates and onion is tender and pale golden, stirring frequently, about 8 minutes.
Add celery and thyme; stir 2 minutes.
Add stock and all potatoes; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 25 minutes.

title: grand marnier sauce de la gruniel
directions: Beat yolks + 1/2 cup sugar in top of double boiler-5-8 minutes, until pale yellow and thick. Remove from heat and stir in Grand Marnier. Cool to room temperature and refrigerate, cover until very cold. Whip cream with 2 tbsp sugar until almost stiff. Fold well into egg yolks. Refrigerate, cover & store. Serve over fresh fruit.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil and let boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and quickly beat in next 4 ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper to cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat together and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cook in crock-pot several hours or in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook to hard ball stage.
Place Marshmallow Creme in mixer bowl. Beat in hot syrup slowly until candy holds shape.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper or buttered plate.

title: cool whip frosting
directions: Mix pudding, milk and powdered sugar with mixer for 1 minute until creamy. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on cake.

title: margie wright's apricot squares
directions: Combine and sift flour and soda.
Cream oleo, gradually adding sugar; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Press 3 cups of this crumbly mixture in bottom and sides of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Spread apricot mixture over crust and sprinkle rest of crumbs over top.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cowboys beans
directions: Cut up onions and brown in pan.
Cube bacon and fry brown hamburger also.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in casserole about 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon supreme
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour and oleo as you do for pie crust.
Put into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: jane's goulash
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess fat.
Add onions, celery and pepper
and
cook
about
5 minutes or until browned.
Add mushrooms,
cheese and eggs and stir to mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and small amount
of
water;
cover
and
simmer
on low heat for 1 hour. Serve over rice or spaghetti with garlic bread and salad.
This has been my children's favorite meal through the years.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: cracker salad
directions: Dice vegetables as small as possible.
(The smaller they are, the better the salad will be.)
Crush both sticks of crackers into the bowl of vegetables.
Mix together well.
Add Miracle Whip. (The amount you use is really up to you and based on your own taste.)
Refrigerate for about 15 minutes before serving.
Feeds around 10.

title: polk greens
directions: Choose tender shoots of polk; wash well.
Have a generous amount of boiling water (enough to cover greens when they are blanched).
Add greens.
Bring back to a boil.
Cook 15 minutes; drain.
Season with bacon drippings.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot.

title: grandma carbonara's zucchini frittata
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs with cheese, pepper and a dash of salt until it is liquid.
Melt butter in a 10 to 12-inch skillet with ovenproof handle.
Melt over high heat until foam subsides.
Pour egg mixture into skillet.
Reduce heat to medium-high. Break air bubbles with a fork.
With back of fork, pull sides of egg mixture to center of pan so liquid runs under cooked eggs. Cook 3 to 4 minutes until bottom is set and top is still liquid.

title: cheese and mushroom matzo kugel
directions: Soak matzos in cold water for 2 minutes.
Remove and squeeze out as much water as possible.
Set aside.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil noodles for 4 minutes.
Fry hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain grease.
In a bowl, mix spaghetti sauce and mushroom soup, undiluted.
In a pan, layer hamburger, noodles, sauce and soup and then top with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Freezes well.
Thaw before baking and bake longer if previously frozen.

title: pinto beans
directions: Look beans over for dirt and rocks, wash real good. Cover beans with water and 1 tbsp soda. Soak overnight. Rinse real good. Cover with water and simmer all day adding water when necessary. Add sugar and salt to taste.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Cut beef, onions, potatoes, and bell pepper into small 1/2 to 1 inch cubes.
Spray a 4 quart soup pot with Pam (or other vegetable cooking spray) and add olive oil.
Brown beef on high, adding black pepper before beef is completely brown.
Add onions and 1/4 cup water, stirring continuously to keep from sticking. Add remaining water, potatoes, green peppers, and spices, and tomatoes, if desired.
Cook for 10 minutes at high. Stir in macaroni.
Reduce heat to low. Add more black pepper to taste. Cover with lid and simmer for 40 minutes. Serves 4-6.
Best served with cornbread or Mom's biscuits.

title: chicken dorito
directions: Mix soups, tomatoes and melted cheese.
Place chicken in dish; sprinkle with onions.
Top with chips.
Pour on soup mixture and top with more chips.
Place on oven; bake at 350° for 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: southern style chicken
directions: You will need 1 oven bag, regular size.

title: sweet and sour spinach salad
directions: Wash and spin dry spinach.
Remove large stems and break into bite size pieces.

title: wild rice soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine celery, mushrooms, onion and oil.
Cook over medium heat; stir occasionally until vegetables are tender (10 to 12 minutes).
Stir in rice, water, soups and bacon.
Reduce heat to low.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.
Stir in milk and wine.
Continue cooking until heated through (2 to 4 minutes).

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: m&m christmas trees
directions: Set aside 1/3 c. of frosting.
Add food coloring to the remaining frosting.
Stir until well blended.
Cover cookie with white frosting.
Stick the cone to the cookie.
Cover entire cone with green frosting.
While frosting is moist, stick the Holiday M&Ms to the cone.
Use mini M&Ms to decorate as colored lights. Use wrapped candy to decorate around the bottom of the tree.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese over bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Spread salsa on top of cream cheese.
Spread Mozzarella cheese on top of salsa.
Bake in 400° oven 15 to 20 minutes until bubbles.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: toasted coconut butterballs
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add flour all at once and blend.
Add coconut, mixing well.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Chill 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Roll in additional powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box. When cake is done, punch holes in the top with a fork. Pour milk and syrup over hot cake. Let cool. Cover with Cool Whip. Crush Butterfinger bar and sprinkle over the top of the cake.

title: date bars
directions: Here's an example of how you can substitute ingredients and adjust amounts to make a holiday recipe more healthful.

title: cream cheese and chili dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in a shallow baking or microwave dish.
Spoon chili onto cream cheese; spread evenly.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or bake until chili begins to bubble.
Serve hot with your favorite tortilla chip.

title: festive sweet potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle over top of sweet potatoes.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: peppermint mallow creme
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme
and
water, mixing until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream and candy.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Wrap and freeze.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Mix in bowl the Russian dressing, apricot preserves, soup mix and water.
Pour mixture over chicken and then cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with pineapple.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: sauce for meatballs
directions: Put in crock-pot with meatballs.

title: southern plantation cake
directions: Mix well cake mix, oleo, coconut, 1 egg and chopped nuts.
Pat into a heavily greased oblong pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Mix well and pour over dough mixture.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: sesame halibut
directions: Combine orange juice, catsup, soy sauce, lemon juice, pepper, sesame oil and honey; mix well.
Place halibut in a shallow baking dish and pour marinade over.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: holly taters
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag.
Soak potatoes in water; drain and coat well with flour mixture.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in pan.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour. Turn potatoes 1 time during baking.

title: brown sugar drop cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and egg.
Add flour to which has been added the salt, soda and sour milk.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the pork chops.
Lay pork chops on top of mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet onion pie
directions: Mix soda crackers with 1/4 c. melted butter.
Put in the bottom of a pie plate.
Saute 2 c. thinly sliced onions in 2 Tbsp. butter until transparent.
Put on top of cracker mixture.
Mix well beaten eggs with milk, seasonings and cheese.
Put on top of onions. Sprinkle with dash of paprika.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4-6.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Coat muffin tin (12 muffins) with Pam.
Stir together first 5 ingredients.
In small bowl, whisk egg whites until frothy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until just moistened.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatball sauce
directions: Combine chili sauce and grape jelly.
Heat until jelly is melted; stir while heating.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes, until sauce thickens.
Add 1 pound of meat balls and simmer until ready to eat.

title: sauerkraut relish *
directions: Drain and chop sauerkraut; mix with celery, pepper, onion and pimento.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and garlic powder. Spread in greased 9-inch dish.
Combine pepperoni, peppers and sauce; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Add Mozzarella and continue baking another 10-15 minutes until cheese is melted and mixture bubbles.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or toasted garlic bread cut into dipping squares.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Open rolls, lay out flat, do not disconnect.
Spread thin layer of sausage on dough.
Roll into a log.
Put in freezer at least 1 hour.
Slice log in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 425° until golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the white sugar, brown sugar and butter together.
Add the eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix together, then add the flour, soda and salt.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with a fork. Bake for 22 minutes at 300°.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: green beans
directions: In a large saucepan, cook meat until brown. Drain off fat. Add green beans, chopped onions, salt and pepper. Cover with water. Bring to a boil on high heat. Reduce heat to medium-high and simmer for 20 minutes. Add additional 3/4 cup of water to green beans and turn to low for 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Place into serving dish. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and onions.
Pour 1 1/2 cups Hidden Valley dressing over vegetables and mix well.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Blend butter, confectioners sugar and flour together.
Spread evenly over bottom of a 10 x 6-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs.
Add brown sugar, baking powder, coconut and pecans.
Mix well and pour over the first mixture.
Bake in
a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix vegetables with pasta, then pour seasonings over them. Let set several hours for flavor to mix.

title: hot wings
directions: Fry unbattered chicken wings in deep fryer until crisp.
While chicken is frying, mix all other ingredients together.
When chicken is done, remove.
Let grease drain from wings, then place in sauce for a few minutes.

title: tearoom rolls
directions: Cook potatoes in 2 cups boiling water. Force hot cooked potatoes through strainer. Add sugar and shortening to potatoes and beat thoroughly. Crumble in yeast; add enough flour to make fairly stiff dough. Knead on floured board about 10 minutes, until dough is smooth and elastic. Put in greased bowl; grease top. Cover with damp cloth. Let rise in warm place until doubled. Shape dough into rolls. Place in greased pan and let rise. Bake in 350° oven.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender; drain and put in large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat until smooth.
Add salt and pepper, then cream cheese and beat again.
Blend in eggs, flour, parsley and grated onion; beat thoroughly.
Check seasonings and turn into buttered casserole.
Spread slightly crushed onions over top and bake uncovered at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes, until puffy and golden.
Casserole may be prepared in the morning and refrigerated until baking time, the onions added just before placing in oven. Serves 8.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 can tomato sauce, mixing well.
Place mixture in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish and shape into a loaf.
Combine remaining tomato sauce and remaining ingredients in a small mixing bowl and pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheeseburger pasta
directions: Brown hamburger. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook until done.

title: pumpkin bread or muffins
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add other ingredients, mix well.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour for 2 large loaves; or bake in muffin tins for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves or 2 to 2 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: pineapple coconut pudding cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 17 x 11-inch cookie sheet at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Make pudding to which you have also beat in cream cheese.
Spread on cake.
Drop on crushed pineapple.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Add finely chopped walnuts; sprinkle coconut. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: christmas eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Slowly add 1/2 cup sugar, a small amount at a time, beating until mixture is smooth; set aside.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add remaining sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spoon beaten egg whites into chilled punch bowl.
Beat whipping cream until foamy. Add powdered sugar and beat until soft peaks form.
Spoon whipped cream on top of beaten egg whites.
Pour egg yolk mixture over this and carefully fold all ingredients together.

title: low-fat, low calorie biscuits
directions: Roll and cut out.
Bake at 500° until brown.
Makes 16 biscuits, 65 calories each and 1.5 grams of fat.

title: chocolate syrup pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar together.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Start in cold oven.

title: maria's banana cupcakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add bananas and egg.
Dissolve soda in water, then add to first mixture.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Fill muffin tins which have been greased.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 18 large or 30 small muffins.

title: oatmeal box cookies
directions: Mix together sugars, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and egg. Then add dry ingredients.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Stir Jell-O, water and strawberries until thawed, add pineapple and bananas.
Pour half in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Cover with 1 cup sour cream.
Add rest of Jell-O and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: emma's applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Dissolve soda in water; add to applesauce.
Add additional spices to butter mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt, then add nuts and raisins to flour mixture and add to other mixture.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
This cake can be served warm with whipped cream or allowed to age.

title: birds nest pudding
directions: Pare 6 apples and take out the cores.
Fill the holes where the cores came out with sugar, after placing the apples in an ovenproof baking dish.
Make a batter of 1 pint milk, 2 tablespoons of flour and 3 eggs.
Pour this over the apples and bake until the fruit is soft.

title: flower pot dirt cake
directions: Note:
Need one plastic flowerpot (8 x 10-inch), silk flowers and candy gummy worms.

title: gorgonzola salad
directions: Combine and refrigerate: lettuce, diced green pepper, onion (chopped fine) and diced celery.

title: ham yam logs
directions: In medium size bowl, gently mix together sweet potatoes, banana and pineapple preserves, being careful not to mash.
Spoon mixture onto ham slices, sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon. Roll and secure with toothpick.
Melt butter in a large skillet; add ham yam logs and cook over medium-low heat until heated through.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix together well and spread on flour tortillas. Roll up jellyroll style and refrigerate until firm. Slice across like a jellyroll and serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk for 2 hours.
Beat eggs and sugar together. Add remaining milk, salt, nutmeg and melted butter.
Sprinkle half of the raisins in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (to cut into squares) or place in a casserole dish (to scoop out).
Place soaked bread on top.
Add remaining raisins.
Pour milk and egg mixture over this.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice dressing
directions: Partially cook rice in salt and water.
Cook sausage in skillet and drain.
Saute vegetables in oleo.
Combine rice, sausage and all vegetables; season to taste.
Add chicken broth to moisten.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one hour yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water well.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Let sit one hour in warm place, covered.
Knead on floured board, roll out and cut rolls.
Place on cookie sheet folded in half. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: keftethes(greek meatballs)
directions: Combine and shape into small balls the meat, onions, mint, crumbs, water, salt and pepper.
Strain tomatoes and chop coarse and put on meatballs.
Dot each with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.

title: fruit basket(second place winner 1989)
directions: Carve the cantaloupe into the shape of a basket and scoop out the fruit; set aside.
Slice into a bowl:
apple, plum, pear, and peach.
Peel and slice orange, and add to other fruit.
Slice cantaloupe and add to fruit, along with walnuts and raisins.
Toss gently.
Put fruit mixture into basket.
Garnish handle of basket with cherry.
Serve.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Chop or crush one large bag of Oreo cookies.
Spread 1/2 of crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all the ingredients together and pour over cookie crumbs.
Spread remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: ham loaf
directions: Blend and mix all ingredients.
Form into a loaf and place in baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
After the first hour, baste with the following mixture.

title: easy rice
directions: Empty soup into a saucepan.
Fill empty soup can half full with Minute rice; add enough water to fill the can.
Combine with soup; quickly bring to a full boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: christmas divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan; bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat; cook to hard-ball stage (252°).
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add dry gelatin gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Pour syrup slowly into egg white mixture, beating constantly until candy holds shape.
Stir in nuts; pour quickly into 9-inch buttered pan.
Let stand until firm.
Dip knife into hot water and cut as desired.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package until tender but not mushy.
Put in greased casserole dish (I use a 9 x 13-inch).
Next, mix onions, celery, cheese and mayonnaise. Spread over vegetables.
Melt margarine; mix with crackers. Sprinkle over top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbles in center.

title: simple chicken
directions: Dry wipe chicken. Dip in 1 tablespoon oil. Shake off excess oil and roll in cracker crumbs. Lay in casserole dish. Shake a little salt and pepper over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili cook off(chili cook off entry - 1994)
directions: Fry sausage and 1/2 of onion; add venison (beef).
Drain off any fat.
Mince onion and fry with meat.
Add canned vegetables and water.
Add spices.
Simmer all day.
Cool in refrigerator. Reheat and serve the next day.
Recipe makes 1 gallon.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Tear cake into very small pieces.
Mix sugar, milk and cream cheese thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add cake, a little at a time and fold into cream cheese and topping mixture. Pat into large 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover with 2 cans pie filling of your choice.
Also delicious with fresh strawberries or peaches. Cool and serve.

title: leftover potatoes
directions: Don't throw your leftover potatoes out.
Mash them together and fry them.
Make potato salad out of them.
Put them in a casserole dish and put cheese on top and bake them.
Potatoes are good and have potassium and there are several ways to fix them.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Slice stick of pepperoni into about 1/4-inch slices, then cube.
Mix everything together and place in a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: glorified hash brown
directions: In large microwave safe bowl, combine soup and cream cheese. Cover and cook on high for 3-4 minutes or until cream cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add the potatoes and stir until coated.

title: the best pie crust
directions: Stir together and roll out on wax paper; delicious!

title: beef tips on rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot and simmer all day. Prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve the beef tips over the rice.
If more gravy is desired, add additional soup.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Cream butter.
Mix sugar, flour and corn meal together, then add to butter.
Add well beaten eggs to butter and sugar mixture. Then, add buttermilk and soda mixture; add vanilla, salt and coconut, if desired.
Pour into unbaked 9 or 10-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° until top is brown and filling is firm.
Bake approximately 35 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream by hand the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery.
Add green beans and cream of chicken soup.
Mix together and pour into casserole. Sprinkle Tater Tots on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana punch bowl cake
directions: This dessert is made in layers in a punch bowl.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375, In 10-inch skillet cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In large bowl blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetables evenly into crust.
Bake at 370 for 18-20 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy oven lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add water, sauce and salt. Bring to a boil. In 2-quart baking dish, layer meat sauce, uncooked noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers, ending with sauce. Garnish with more Parmesan cheese and cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 375°. Season to taste with Italian seasoning.

title: crustless pineapple pie
directions: In a blender, combine the milk, sugar, biscuit mix, butter, eggs, vanilla and food coloring if desired; cover and process until smooth.
Sprinkle the pineapple into a greased deep-dish 9-in. pie plate.
Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Garnish with whipped topping if desired.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in flour.
Add coconut, then add to batter.
Cook in tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs with sugar; add milk, salt and corn.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Dot with butter.
Place in 350°
oven and cook until thick and golden, approximately 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage in process mixer the thinness you wish or shred by	hand

or large grater.	Mix cabbage, chopped pepper, minced onion and carrots in bowl.	In small bowl whisk together vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper for about 1 minute until sugar dissolves.	Whisk in vegetable and olive oil until well mixed. Refrigerate
at
least
1 hour or up to 24 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Put all of the ingredients into a bowl.
Whisk with an electric beater.
Add milk a little at a time until the mixture is smooth and creamy.
Pour mixture in greased cake tins.
Bake at 180°C for 30 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli beef
directions: Marinate meat in mixture.
Saute 4 cups cut-up broccoli over high heat, stir-frying 2 to 3 minutes.
Add a few drops of water to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 tablespoon oil and stir-fry marinated meat until partially cooked.
Turn down heat; add broccoli and gravy.

title: doughnuts
directions: Roll the dough to 1/2-inch on floured board.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Lay on plate as you cut them.
Fry in cast-iron pan.
Add a cube of fresh bread to oil.
When it browns, oil is ready.
Cook at medium temperature, 3 to 5 minutes and turn. Drain on paper towels.
Sugar at once.
Easy!

title: steak n' veggies with dipping sauce
directions: Place veggies, cut side up, on waxed paper; drizzle with olive oil.
Place beef steak on one side of rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 3 to 4 inches from heat.
Arrange onion and potato wedges on other side.
Broil 16 to 18 minutes until steak is medium (160°) and potatoes and onions are tender.

title: chocolate dipped fruits
directions: Melt 8 ounces semi-sweet chocolate with 2 tablespoons vegetable shortening in microwave.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon orange extract.
Dip fresh fruits in mixture.
Allow to set on wax paper.

title: shamrock pie
directions: Combine water, gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar, egg yolks, lime juice and food coloring in saucepan; bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; place saucepan in pan of ice water. Cool until thickened.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In large pan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook over high heat 5 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add butter and 2 1/3 cups pecans.
Cook until this forms a soft ball in cool water.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly, then beat until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Decorate with pecan halves.

title: quick oatmeal chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and salt to a boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.
Yields 36 cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread chicken (or ground meat) in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread stuffing on top of chicken, then spread soup over stuffing. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve immediately!
Quick, easy and delicious!

title: angel food pie
directions: Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until mixture stands alone.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Place in a slow oven (300°) and bake until whites are slightly browned, about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Whip cream, add 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spread evenly over cooled pie.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.

title: pasta fagul(serves 3 to 4)
directions: In large saucepan, combine oil and garlic.
Saute until brown. Add next 3 ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour (also basil, salt and pepper).
Add 1/2 hot water and beans; heat thoroughly.
Cook pasta; add just before serving.
Serve with crusty bread and garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: snappers
directions: On buttered baking sheet, arrange 72 pecan halves, flat side down, in piles of 4.
Place 2 caramels on each cluster of pecans (takes 36 caramels).
Heat in slow oven (325°) until caramels soften, about 8 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup over low heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk until it comes to a soft ball stage. Stir in vanilla and add popcorn.
Roll into balls.
Have fun!

title: lemon walnut tea bread
directions: In large bowl cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Beat into creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in walnuts and lemon rind.
Spoon into greased 8-1/2 x 4-1/2 x 2-1/2 inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 55-60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack to cool completely. Drizzle with lemon icing and sprinkle with additional walnuts.

title: potato salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, add potatoes, celery, onions and salt.
In a separate bowl, mix mayo, oil, vinegar, mustard and paprika.
Mix and add to potatoes.
Toss lightly.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: beef quesadillas
directions: Saute onion.
Brown beef and drain.
Combine onion, beef, picante and chilies.
Put spoonful in center of tortilla and sprinkle with cheese.
Brown on both sides on griddle or on cookie sheet in the oven.

title: tired of making chocolate chip cookies cookie
directions: Mix in order. Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes. (Can also add 1/2 cup coconut between oatmeal and sour milk.)

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients (corn meal, sugar, baking powder, flour and salt).
Add shortening, egg and enough milk to make a thin batter. Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a hot 425° oven.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Melt chocolate and add whole egg.
Add 3 egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Beat egg whites with sugar until stiff. Add to chocolate mix.
Whip cream until stiff and fold in.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: apricot-peach torte(serves 8)
directions: In a food processor, turn the zwieback crackers into crumbs. Pat 2/3 of the crumbs into the bottom of a well-buttered 8-inch spring-form pan.
Drain peaches and apricots. Place the peach halves, cut side up, on crumbs.
Fill in the spaces with the apricot halves, keeping 3 aside for garnish.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and let set.
Scald milk and shortening together.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and rest of the ingredients.
Work good; shape into rolls.
Place in greased pan and grease tops of rolls and let rise, covered, in a warm place for 3 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° until tops are brown. Place on rack to cool, grease tops and cover.

title: chess cake
directions: Melt brown sugar and butter on low heat, then add other things. Cook about 1 hour at 300° in sheet cake pan.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Melt margarine in deep baking pan; add flour mixture.
Do not stir!
Spoon pie filling onto mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Yummy!

title: granola
directions: Mix in large flat pan and bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours or until browned.
Stir occasionally.

title: cheese blintz(a sweet snack)
directions: *Whatever amount it takes to coat outside of rolls.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: clams casino
directions: Wash clams and open.
Loosen the clam from the shell.
Place clams in shell, on cookie sheet.

title: curried yogurt sauce(for broiled fish)
directions: Mix ingredients together in the order given.
Broil fish until just tender.
Place 1 tablespoon of curried yogurt sauce on top of each serving of fish.
Broil fish a minute longer.
Remove fish to serving platter.
Serve remaining sauce in separate container.

title: chicken marsala(yields 4 servings)
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Saute garlic until golden.
Add onions and heat until transparent.
Add sliced mushrooms; cook until slightly tender.
Lightly pepper each side of fillet. (Sprinkle meat with flour on both sides; this will thicken the broth.)
Saute both sides until meat is cooked.
Add chicken broth with Parmesan cheese and cook until liquid thickens.
When liquid broth is consistency of gravy, add Marsala wine and lower heat to slow simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Enjoy!

title: classic salsa
directions: Mix all together and let set for 2 hours.
Serve with nachos or tortilla chips.

title: strawberry ambrosia
directions: In a large bowl, combine the ingredients, adding the strawberries last.

title: pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Combine pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine.

title: spinach parmesan
directions: Cook the cleaned spinach until tender; drain thoroughly.
Chop coarsely and add the cheese, onion, cream and 4 tablespoons of the butter.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish and sprinkle the crumbs, mixed with the remaining butter.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix as directed on
cake
mix.	One cup chocolate chips may be stirred in after mixing.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for
to 60 minutes.
Melt 1/2 cup White Chocolate Icing or	any
flavor
icing, and drizzle over cooled cake.

title: pralines
directions: Grease a 2 foot long sheet of wax paper.
Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring mixture to boil; continue cooking over high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage, 238°
Remove the pan from heat and continue stirring as the candy cooks.
When the mixture becomes creamy and cloudy and the pecans remain suspended while stirring, remove the cinnamon sticks.
Quickly spoon the mixture onto the wax paper before the candy hardens in the pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and margarine, mixing well.
Pour into one 3-quart baking dish.
Combine margarine and bread crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and hot.

title: traditional fudge
directions: To keep coffee from being bitter, place 1 inch of cold water in pot before brewing.

title: english taffy(like heath candy bars)
directions: Mix the sugar, butter, corn syrup and water.
Cook until 290° or few drops crack in cold water.
Chop the Hershey bar finely. Put 1/2 cup nut meats in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour syrup over nuts.
Put the 1/4 cup ground nuts on top and candy bar on top of nuts.
Cool and break in pieces.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine apples, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Dot with small pieces of butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over pretzel mix; seal edges.
Refrigerate.
Mix Jell-O in hot water and add strawberries, stirring to defrost.
Refrigerate until it begins to thicken. Mix well and pour over cheese mixture. Serves 12.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all together and use large casserole dish.
Mix 1 package Ritz cracker crumbs (fine) and 1 stick melted butter together and put on top of green bean mixture.
Cook for 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: jam brown-and-serve rolls* * * * *
directions: The Frittata recipe came from a magazine that
I copied when we were living in Arizona.
It reminds me of a Basque omelet I used to make years ago that used leftover vegetables.
The red peppers actually make a prettier dish.

title: baked chicken with almonds
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Cut the broiler-fryer into 4 portions; dredge with flour and place on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Brush with 1/4 cup of melted butter and bake at 400° until browned, 25 to 35 minutes.
When the chicken is brown, remove the rack.
Place the chicken in the bottom of the pan and add the chicken stock to a depth of 1/2-inch.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date cream pie
directions: Mix first six ingredients and cook together.
Add dates after filling is cooked.
Put in a cooked pie shell.
Make a meringue from the 2 whites and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Place on top.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: skillet squash au gratin
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add squash, onion, salt, pepper and water.
Cook, covered, 10 to 15 minutes or until squash is tender. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: pizza bread
directions: Cook meat, onions and garlic salt until browned. Add spices and tomato sauce. Toast bread. Spoon on meat mixture. Sprinkle on cheese. Put in 400° oven until cheese melts. Add sliced ripe olives and mushrooms, if desired.

title: grandma tessie peach cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together first six items.
Press into a 10-inch pie dish.
Peel and slice peaches; arrange in rows on crust in pie dish.
Beat eggs with 3/4 cup sugar.
Pour over the peaches.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and cream cheese in mixer.
Add sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in shell.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup. Freeze.
Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes before slicing.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter in oven and remove.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add flour, milk and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add cheese, thawed spinach and onion. Pour into pan and bake 35 minutes.
Remove and cool 45 minutes to set.
Cut into bite size pieces.
To freeze, place on cookie sheet.
When frozen, transfer to plastic bag.
To reheat, bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Makes 35 to 45 pieces.

title: pig feet with sauerkraut
directions: In heavy kettle, arrange bed of sauerkraut.
Sprinkle onions and seasonings.
Place pig feet on sauerkraut bed and add bouillon.
Bring liquid to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, tightly covered, for 2 1/2 hours or until the pig feet are tender enough for meat to fall off bones.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, onions and peppers.
Sprinkle salt over them. Let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Mix spices, vinegar and sugar in a large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over pickles.
Cold pack for 20 minutes.

title: yiayia's rice
directions: For every cup of
rice, add these ingredients.	Add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french cocoa balls
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar well.
Blend into milk.
Add nuts and vanilla and mix well.
Roll into small balls, then roll in the cocoa and powdered sugar.

title: bread sticks
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; blend well.
In small saucepan or in a microwave, heat water and oil until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in an additional 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour until dough pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl.

title: cucumber sandwich spread
directions: Drain cucumbers well.
Add onion.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve on any kind of bread.
Makes a nice party sandwich spread.
May top with a very thin slice of cucumber.

title: vernal's punch
directions: Melt sugar and Kool-Aid in a small amount of heated water. Mix with juice and the remaining water.
Freeze in a plastic milk jug.
Thaw slightly and chop.
Add ginger ale to serve.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat in large frying pan.
Drain fat.
Add celery, tomatoes, tomato paste, water, seasonings, green pepper, bouillon and rice.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put mixture into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Add water or tomato juice if necessary.
Stir occasionally.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put pork chops in baking dish.
Pour onion soup on pork chops. Add mushrooms.
Add sliced potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with Reynolds Wrap and bake at least 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 7 minutes.
Add marshmallow, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Stir.
Pour into pan and refrigerate.

title: seashell macaroni casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef, green pepper, onions and garlic in the butter.
Add the pepper, mushrooms and liquid, cheese, salt, sugar, Worcestershire, chili powder and corn.
Mix macaroni with beef mixture and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix above ingredients well.
Put in unbaked 8 or 9-inch pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Make a few slits in crust.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 1 hour).

title: pecan topped grahams
directions: In small saucepan heat margarine and brown sugar over low heat until margarine is melted.
Stir in syrup and nuts.
Spread on top of each graham cracker.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool.
Store tightly covered.
These freeze well.

title: chilled fruit salad
directions: Place lemon juice in a large bowl and add sweetened condensed milk; mix well.
Add whipped topping; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
While meat is browning, cook noodles.
After draining meat, add spaghetti sauce and mix.
In a large casserole dish, layer noodles, meat sauce and cheese (cottage cheese can be added in the layers, if desired).
Top the layers off with extra cheese on top.
Place into oven until cheese melts into a golden brown at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swanky frankies
directions: Split dogs lengthwise without cutting through.
Broil or grill dogs.
Put 1/2 teaspoon onion and 1/2 slice cheese in split, wrap dog with bacon and broil or microwave only until cheese melts.
Put dog in bun and add favorite condiments.

title: quick and easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken (or parts); remove from bone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Cube Velveeta cheese and add to the soups.
Heat until cheese melts.
Drain spaghetti, add the soup mixture.
Heat in oven until warm.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Place 1/2 tomatoes in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Top with 1/2 of each of the onion, cheese and bread crumbs.
Repeat layers.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over the top of the tomato mixture.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for an additional 10 minutes.

title: cold pepsi
directions: Fill glass with ice cubes, pour Pepsi over and serve to Dad.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage; cook for 7 minutes in boiling salted water to cover.
Drain; cool.
Remove 12 large outer leaves.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate.
Make a couple hours ahead of use.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat the yolks.
Add the sugar and beat.
Add the rye or bourbon, rum and brandy.
Add the milk and table cream.
Just before serving, fold in the beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Serves 20.

title: hershey chocolate cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture with syrup.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; brown onion, green pepper and meat. Mix in other ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chinese salad
directions: Let frozen peas thaw in their boxes.
Wash and drain lettuce. In a large bowl, fill with lettuce, torn in large sections.
Slice onion into rings and toss with lettuce.
Add peas and boiled egg slices.
When nearly ready to serve, add dressing and seasoning and toss.
When ready to serve, add fried noodles and toss and serve.
Serves 6.

title: popcorn caramel crunch
directions: In a large greased bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine sugar, butter, corn syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches soft crack stage (280° to 290°).
Remove from the heat.
Stir in cinnamon.

title: 8 can soup
directions: Put beef in 5-quart crock-pot uncooked and dump each can undrained.
Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse shrimp and set aside.
Blend cheese, milk and mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients including shrimp and chill. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco together, beating until light. Add eggs, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla, mixing well.
Start cake in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in a greased tube pan.

title: ham and red-eye gravy
directions: Note:
Coffee may contain cream and sugar, just as you would drink it.

title: mary's cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine until lightly browned.
Scald milk and broth together.
Add flour to vegetables, mixing well. Add boiling water and scalded milk to broth.
Stir well.
Tear cheese into small pieces and microwave until melted, careful not to burn.
Add to mixture.
Never let water boil in a double boiler (soup will curdle if heated too fast).
I add my melted cheese and cook in pan over low heat only a few minutes as cheese is already melted.
Serve with Toasties.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: fluffy orange pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk, then juice until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust. Chill.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes; do not pare.
Cook in boiling water until tender, using 1 teaspoon salt to each quart of water.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel and chop.
To drippings in pan, add flour and blend.
Gradually stir in water and vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it boils and thickens. Add salt, sugar and onions.
Peel and dice hot potatoes.
Add bacon and pour hot dressing over it.
Mix lightly.
Add parsley. Serve hot.

title: glorified rice
directions: Prepare the rice. Mix with sugar, marshmallows and almonds (or coconut). Fold in whipped topping. Mix well. Chill well before serving.

title: joan's cheesecake
directions: Beat ingredients, one at a time, beating smooth after each addition.

title: homemade barbecue ham
directions: Wash pork shoulder very good and cut out as much fat as you can.
If it is fat, you can get it out.
Mash fresh tomatoes, cut up celery in small pieces and cut up onions in small pieces. Slice the lemons up in cubes, mash garlic or cut it up.
Put all tomatoes, sauce, hot sauce, ketchup, onions, celery, lemons, pepper, thyme, garlic, basil and bay leaf in 3-quart pan and cook for 2 to 3 hours on medium heat.
After it cooks, put ham that is washed in large cooking pan; pour barbecue sauce over meat and bake in hot 350° oven until meat falls from bone, 3 to 4 hours, depending on size of ham 4 to 5 hours.
Hum-hum-good; better than Campbell's soup.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Mix and serve on lettuce or use as sandwiches.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Remove. Add onion and green pepper. Cook slowly until onion is soft and yellow.
Crumble bacon.
When onion and pepper are tender, add all other ingredients in a greased casserole dish and stir. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese just before done, if desired.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute cabbage, celery, onions, carrots and garlic in butter in big pan.
Add everything else and let cook for 1 hour.

title: baked oysters
directions: Shuck oysters; drain and reserve half of the shells. Combine parsley, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, clam juice and chili sauce with 6 Tbsp. melted butter. Dip each oyster into this sauce and place in a shell on a baking pan. Spoon remaining sauce over oysters. Sprinkle a tsp. of chopped mushrooms on each oyster. Stir cheese and bread crumbs together and sprinkle over oysters. Dribble remaining butter. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: wheat honey loaf with pecans
directions: Makes 1 (8-inch) loaf.

title: tornado cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
On the bottom of the pan, spread coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Then spread cake mixture in bottom of pan. Blend powdered sugar, cream cheese and oleo together.
(May need a little water to make spreadable.) Mix and marble through cake. Bake in the pan for 55 minutes.

title: chocolate peppermint creams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Heat brown sugar, butter and water.
Add morsels and stir to melt.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto cookie sheet lined with greased, super-strength Alcoa wrap (aluminum).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes and cool. Makes 8 dozen sandwiches.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion, carrot and peas in the order listed. In a 9 x 13-inch dish. Spread with the mayonnaise, sealing to the edges. Sprinkle with the sugar, cheese and bacon. Chill tightly covered for 8-10 hours.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Dip onions (Spanish onions preferred) in batter; deep fry and enjoy.

title: snows' spanish rice
directions: Optional:
Substitute 1 cup milk for 1 can tomato soup.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar.
Sift flour, tartar, soda and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly and roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stewed okra-tomato-onion
directions: Cut up the okra, peel onion and tomatoes.
Add a very small amount of water.
Cook them just until tender.
Season with heavy cream and salt.
A little fresh corn and a few lima beans may also be added.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding celery seed to taste, in blender or food processor.
Store in refrigerator; this will not separate. Use as dressing for any raw vegetable salad.
Makes 3 cups.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add other ingredients.
Place in large casserole (about a 2 1/2-quart).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes or until done, in unbaked pie crust.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave margarine in 4-quart microwave dish on HIGH 1 minute. Add sugar and milk; mix well. Microwave 5 minutes or until mixture begins to boil, stirring after 3 minutes.
