Scrape down sides of bowl. Microwave another 5 1/2 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes. Add milk chocolate chips; stir until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 glass pan. Cool at room temperature before cutting.

title: white coconut christmas pie
directions: Make a pie crust, baked, with high fluted edge.
Blend thoroughly in a saucepan flour, sugar, gelatin and salt.
Stir in gradually 1 3/4 cups milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Place pan in cold water.
Cool until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Blend in the flavorings.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks. Carefully fold in stiffly whipped cream and coconut.
Pile into pie crust; sprinkle with coconut.
Chill several hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix together.
Pour over 8 to 10 pieces of chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with white rice.

title: seafoam fruit cake filling
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and
water and boil.
Spread on cake layers. Beat egg whites; put syrup over fruit and nuts.
Boil raisins 10 or 15 minutes.
Drain.
Pour syrup over raisins.
Add fruit and nuts.
Add egg whites last.

title: italian cream cake(yields 16 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Butter	and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and blend into butter mixture.
Mix in	buttermilk,
coconut,
pecans
and
vanilla. Pour into pans. Bake for
30 minutes.
Test with cake tester. If using 9-inch pans, invert onto racks and cool.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix with pastry blender until crumbly.
Divide into 4 equal parts and form into balls.
Each ball will make 12 small balls. Press into small muffin tins.

title: barbecue bean bake
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion. Drain. Combine with remaining ingredients except beans. Stir well. Add beans and combine thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes; cut off tops and scoop out pulp.
Invert on paper towel and drain.

title: mother's corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease well an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine dry ingredients; make a well in the center. Blend egg, milk and oil in small bowl, then pour into dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened. Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form into a ball.
Refrigerate until using.
Spread on crackers.

title: potato salad(mother)
directions: Cook and mash potatoes with cream, salt, pepper and butter. Use 5 eggs.
Add vinegar and cook until thick.
Add onion, sugar and pickle juice.
Add 4 boiled eggs to top.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients.	Make
a
well and add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: sausage bean soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook sausage, onion and garlic until sausage is browned. Drain. Add beans, tomatoes, broth and basil. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans. Combine all wet ingredients. Add all dry ingredients and mix until moist. Pour into pans and bake 25 minutes. Cool and remove from pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until cooked, save broth.
Remove skin and debone.
Break into bite-size pieces.
Crush crackers and melt butter; mix.
Mix soup, sour cream and 1 cup chicken broth.
Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 of cracker mix on bottom. Place chicken pieces on top of crackers.
Pour soup mix on top of chicken.
Top with remaining cracker mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: brother edmund's fried apple fritters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, water, milk and sugar in a small mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Core and slice apples crosswise 1/8-inch thick, leaving skins on.
Dip each apple slice in batter and tap against side of bowl to remove excess.
Heat oil in a 12-inch skillet until very hot.
Add slices being careful not to crowd skillet.
Brown on both sides and drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Makes 15 slices.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook oil, hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add tomato sauce, water and salt.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Put over it cheese.
Cook 10 minutes longer.

title: mushroom-artichoke soup
directions: Simmer ingredients 10 minutes.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Beat egg yolks and sugar together.
Add milk, lemon juice and rind, flour and butter.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into a 1-quart baking dish (greased).
Set in shallow pan of water and bake at 350° until firm, approximately 30 minutes.
Has a firm cake on top and soft pudding in bottom.

title: fried zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Combine the flour, meal and sugar in a bowl.
Slice the tomatoes and zucchini in a bowl of water.
Dip each slice in the flour mixture.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: lois' golden fried chicken strips
directions: Wash and cut chicken into 1-inch strips. Place flour, salt and pepper into plastic Ziploc bag. Add chicken and shake well. Place breaded chicken in frying pan in about 1-inch deep oil. Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt and garlic powder. Fry for 4 minutes on both sides. Keep turning until golden brown.

title: burgundy chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 2-inch chunks.
Cut carrots into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Peel and cut potatoes into 2-inch chunks.
Coarsely chop onion.
In skillet, medium-high heat, in 2 tablespoons hot olive oil, cook chicken until golden brown.
Remove.
In drippings and 1 more teaspoon olive oil, cook carrots, potatoes and onions until browned.
Stir in red wine.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in stewed tomatoes and 1 1/2 cups water.
Over high heat, heat until boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Mix flour and 2 tablespoons water in a cup.
Stir flour mixture, peas and chicken into skillet.
Over high heat, heat until boiling.
Boil until mixture is thickened. Serves 4 main dishes.

title: peppermint topped fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil; butter the foil.
In medium saucepan, combine 2 tablespoons butter, milk, sugar and salt. Cook over medium heat until boils.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove and stir in marshmallows.
Pour in foil.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread on fudge.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Sprinkle peppers and onions over cucumbers.
Let stand one hour or until liquid develops.
Drain off water and pack in jars. Heat sugar, vinegar and celery seed until sugar is dissolved. Pour over cucumbers, seal and put in refrigerator.

title: lazy pierogi casserole
directions: Boil noodles.
After sauerkraut is cooked, saute it with chopped onions in pork fat or margarine.
Mix noodles with sauerkraut, mushrooms and undiluted soup in casserole.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°, covered.

title: mom's raisin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Combine all liquid ingredients and add to dry ingredients slowly.
Mixture will be stiff.
Drain raisins.
Add to batter.
Divide into 2 greased and floured 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: muscadine sauce
directions: Wash pulps and mix hulls.
Cover and cook slowly for several hours.
Will burn easily.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. In a bowl, mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Spread mixture on top of bean dip layer.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together.
Spread over avocado layer.
Layer onions, tomatoes, black olives and jalapeno peppers over sour cream mixture.
Top with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: holiday spread
directions: Blend all ingredients together, cover with chopped walnuts. Mix together and chill overnight.
Serve with Ritz crackers or Club crackers.

title: rice casserole
directions: Drain mushrooms; heat in skillet with margarine.
Put rice in casserole.
Pour mushrooms and butter over rice.
Then add soup and water.
Stir.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend together first 7 ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the meat; drain off fat.
Cook the noodles according to package directions.
Add the sauce to meat; let simmer.

title: morning shake-up
directions: In blender container or food processor bowl with metal blade, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth.
Yields 1 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: tangy mustard topping
directions: Combine mayonnaise, onion and mustard.
Mix well and pour over cooked vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cook in microwave, uncovered, one minute to heat topping and melt cheese. Use as a topping on cooked vegetables such as cauliflower, broccoli or squash.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion and taco seasoning mix according to directions on package.
Line a dish with the nacho chips.
Cover the chips with the ground beef.
Heat the cheese soup/dip according to directions and pour over the ground beef. Garnish with lettuce, tomato, black olives and sour cream.

title: yogurt pie(from a greek cookbook)
directions: Cream the cream cheese, then mix in next 4 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Blend margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Start adding flour a small amount at a time.
Add eggs and the rest of flour, vanilla and milk.
Cook in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Warm nuts in a 350° oven.
Butter a cookie sheet.
Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil. Remove cover, place thermometer in pan and cook without stirring to 290°.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts, butter, salt and vanilla.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet and spread as thinly as possible.
Cool completely and break into pieces.
Makes 5 cups.

title: cherry breeze(no cook filling, no bake crust)
directions: Mix corn flake crumbs and margarine thoroughly in a 9-inch pie pan.
Press firmly and evenly over bottom and sides of pan to form crust.
Chill.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add condensed milk and blend well.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
Do not freeze. Top with chilled cherry pie filling before serving.
Serves 8.

title: icy pear soup(anjou pears are wonderful in this recipe.)
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add leeks and celery; saut for 5 minutes or until soft. Add potatoes, stock and pepper. Bring to a boil.

Reduce heat and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are soft. Cool slightly. Carefully puree in a food processor or blender until smooth. Add pears and puree. Pour into a large bowl. Stir in milk and nutmeg. Chill thoroughly, at least 2 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate pan cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into large bowl.
In saucepan, melt butter, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into greased 11 x 16 x 1/2-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: You will need a 6-cup baking dish.

title: volina's baked pineapple
directions: Break 4 slices of bread and mix with melted margarine; set aside.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour and crushed pineapple.
Pour over bread mixture in casserole dish.
Break 2 slices of bread and put on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Next, add coloring and vanilla.
Now, add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together, alternately with buttermilk.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Prepare jello and water; chill until syrupy.
Beat in the orange sherbet.
Add the mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Measure and set aside oats, peanut butter and nuts.
Mix in a saucepan, sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Boil no longer than 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper or in greased pan.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve when hard.

title: bath salts
directions: In food processor or blender, mix 4 parts Epsom salts and 1 part baking soda (2 cups Epsom salts equal 1/2 cup baking soda. Blend only a few seconds.
Add 1 drop food coloring and 1 drop perfume.
Blend briefly until color and fragrance are distributed evenly.
Spoon into jars or plastic bags.
Hand lettered instructions may be added.
Add 1/2 cup to running bath water. Also may decorate jars.

title: english strawberry trifle dessert
directions: Layer first half of square cut Jell-O over pieces of angel food cake (or ladyfingers) and then half of the strawberries, layer over cake.
Next, put half of the prepared pudding.
Add half of the Cool Whip.
Last, repeat again Jell-O, cake, strawberries and pudding and top with rest of Cool Whip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook yellow squash, onion, salt and pepper until tender. Drain and mash.
Add chicken soup, sour cream and grated carrots.

title: russian tea
directions: Make the dry ingredients (mix) at home and bring along in a plastic bag.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together until smooth; make into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet; press flat with potato masher.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.

title: 8 ball's guacamole
directions: Take onions, chilies, cilantro and salt and put in food processor. (Do not puree.) Then mix in avocados and everything else. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oatmeal-chocolate-raisin-nut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light golden brown. Cool one minute on cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: outstanding oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and the 2 sugars; blend well. Add egg and stir.
Sift together the flour, soda and cinnamon; add to the first mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Make walnut size pieces of dough; place on cookie sheet.
Butter the bottom of a small glass and dip into white sugar.
Use glass to flatten each piece of dough.
Continue with each piece of dough.
There is no need to re-butter the glass.
Do re-dip in sugar before each pressing.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: jiffy dessert
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a square 8-inch pan.
Spread cake mix over top.
Dribble melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple strudel coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Sift together flour, soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown onion, celery and meat for 20 minutes or until ground beef is done.
In an ovenproof dish (approximately 10 cup size dish).
Mix cream of mushroom soup and water together and add the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until the rice tastes done.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Cook beef and onion in a skillet until meat is browned, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain off pan drippings.
Stir in tomato sauce and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: maui chicken
directions: Combine broth, white wine, sherry, sugar and cornstarch in 2 c. measure.
Stir thoroughly.
Cook on HI for 1 1/2-2 minutes or until sauce is clear, stirring once; set aside.
Combine chicken, green and red peppers, green onions, bamboo shoots and ginger in 2 quart casserole.
Cover and cook on HI for 6 minutes.
Add pineapple, cashews and sauce mixture.
Cover and cook on HI for 2-3 minutes or until hot.
4 servings.
Total cooking time:
9 1/2-11 minutes.

title: chicken in shells
directions: Mix ingredients except soup and shells.
Cook, drain and cool the shells.
Stuff with mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish. Combine 1 can of water with the 2 cans of soup.
Pour over shells. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake covered 1 hour at 350°.
May freeze cooked or uncooked.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients except oil and celery seed; blend until smooth.
On low speed, continue blending, slowly adding oil.
Stir in celery seed.
Cover; chill. Serve with salad of lettuce and sliced sweet onion if desired. Makes about 1 cup.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In large bowl stir first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour onto frozen pie crust.
Bake on cookie sheet 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: boston baked beans
directions: You will need a 2-quart bean pot.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover with mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: luscious salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: quick vegetables and beef
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, heat oil.
Add broccoli and cook until tender-crisp.
Add soup, Worcestershire sauce
and rice.
Heat through.
Serves 2.
Prep. Time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
10 minutes.

title: cheese krisps
directions: Pour melted butter over cheese and flour in bowl.
Add Rice Krispies, pecans and red pepper.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls; flatten on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with celery salt.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight container. Flavor improves with age.

title: cucumber yogurt salad
directions: Peel and chop cucumbers medium fine.
Add garlic and salt to yogurt.
Add cucumbers and garnish with dried mint.

title: butterscotch rice krispie squares
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter together in the microwave until melted.
Stir in Rice Krispies cereal.
Spread mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening together.
Spread on top of mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Add parsley flakes, bouillon cube, seasonings, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and eggs; beat well.

title: turnip soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Saute onion; add peeled and chopped vegetables.
Add chicken stock.
Simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Reserve 1 1/2 cup vegetables.
Puree the rest.
Return to vegetables; add cream.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and bake in pie shell at 325° for 1 hour.

title: reuben soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the onions and celery in butter until tender.
Add broths and baking soda.
Combine cornstarch and water and add to pan.
Bring to a boil; boil for two minutes, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat.
Add sauerkraut, cream and corned beef; simmer and stir for 15 minutes.
Add cheese;
heat until melted.
Add salt and pepper.
Garnish with croutons, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in greased baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
well
in
large bowl and bake in muffin tins
as needed at 400° for 25 minutes.
Keeps 3 weeks, uncooked, in refrigerator.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put potatoes (frozen hash browns) in 13 x 9-inch dish and
let thaw.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Put mixture over potatoes.
Dice one small onion and grate cheese and put over next.
Crush corn flakes to make 2 cups and put over next.
Slice one stick of margarine and put over next.
Cook, covered, 1 1/2 hours, uncovered for the last 1/4 hour to brown at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and immediately add the margarine and vanilla.
Continue cooking until mixture reaches the hard ball stage.
Add the peanut butter and immediatley remove mixture from heat.
Beat until peanut butter is dissolved.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; should bubble all over.
Serves 4.

title: austin's fruit salad
directions: Mix everything together and put in refrigerator until time to eat.

title: turkey macaroni bake
directions: In a large bowl combine turkey, macaroni, 1 1/2 c. cheese, soup, milk, mushrooms and pepper.
Pour into 2 qt. baking dish. Cover and bake 350° 60-65 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5-10 minutes longer until cheese is melted. 6 servings.

title: salmon patties
directions: Squash ingredients together, mixing well.
Form into patties. Fry in skillet, both sides, until completely cooked.

title: pumpkin cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Beat until all is blended together well.
Then add 3/4 cup crushed English walnuts; blend well.
Don't grease or flour 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash browns quiche
directions: Press hash browns between paper to remove excess moisture. Press into the bottom and up on sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Combine the ham, cheese and green pepper.
Spoon over crust.

title: squash casserole *
directions: Stew squash and onion, mash fine.
Add eggs and other ingredients, reserving portion of cheese and bread crumbs for topping.
Mix well and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cholesterol free pound cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add eggs, a little at a time. Mix well after each addition.
Add salt, baking powder, lemon flavoring and vanilla.
Alternate milk and flour; mix well but do not overbeat.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in a greased and floured tube pan.
Do not open oven door until cake is done.

title: barbecue rub
directions: Combine all ingredients well and sprinkle lightly on meat to be grilled.
Rub into meat and allow to sit at room temperature about 1 hour.
Also great on steamed vegetables.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Spread pie filling in square cake pan.
Mix flour, sugar and beaten egg until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Dribble 5 tablespoons of melted margarine over topping.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Good served warm with ice cream.

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat well 2 cups sugar and margarine. Add and beat well the egg yolks. Add alternately sifted flour, salt and baking powder with milk. Then add pecans and lemon zest.	Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Add the green beans, carrots, mushrooms, yellow beans and water chestnuts.

title: "kid friendly spinach balls"
directions: Add drained spinach to beaten eggs and mix well.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels in water.
Combine oats, flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Add margarine.
Mix until crumbly. Save 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Press remainder into bottom of pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over partially baked base.
Drizzle caramel over nuts and chips. Crumble reserved mixture over caramel.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes longer.
My favorite.

title: hot crab meat spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat in Pyrex dish for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers and chilled white wine.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased pan (pie plate).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: canegi(golf ball dumplings)
directions: In a large bowl, cut up bread into small squares and cut salami into cubes.
Add garlic.
Mix up and add flour, cheese, salt, pepper, parsley and enough water to make a dough that won't stick to hands.
Add onions to chicken broth.
Make round "golf balls" with dough and drop in soup that is now at a rolling boil. Cook for 20 minutes.
When dumplings rise to top of soup, they are done (about 20 to 25 minutes).

title: coconut cream custard
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt (dry).
Add a little milk to mix.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Leave rest of milk come to a boil. Mix hot milk into cornstarch mixture by tablespoon until mixture is warm.
Stir mixture into hot milk.
Cook until thick; turn off burner.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into baked crust.
Use whites of eggs for meringue and brown.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a large microwave bowl, mix butter (melted), sugar and milk.
Microwave for 10 minutes on High.
Stir every 2 1/2 minutes and scrape sides of bowl.
Then take mixture out of the microwave and stir in Marshmallow Creme, semi-sweet morsels and vanilla; mix well until completely blended.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown cut-up steak in oil; add cornstarch, then add the rest of ingredients and simmer.
Put peppers and tomatoes in last for a few minutes. Serve over white rice.

title: holiday breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage until cooked and crumbly.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread and stir.
Add cheese, mushroom and sausage.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: one-pan spaghetti(low calorie)
directions: An easy dish for children.

title: frosty fill-up(beverage)
directions: Combine.
Put one scoop orange, lime, pineapple sherbet in large glass, then pour combined juice until glass is filled.
Serve with a spoon or straw.
Serves 8.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat and let cool. Add sugar, molasses and egg and mix well. Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger and cinnamon and add to first mixture; mix well and chill. Form into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar. Place on well-greased cookie sheet. Bake in 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes. (Very good while they are warm.)

title: making tortillas
directions: Mix until dough forms a firm ball. Make 16 small balls. Place each ball between two sheets of waxed paper. Roll out, then peel off the waxed paper. Cook at 440° to 480° in a skillet or griddle for 15 to 30 seconds. Turn over; cook 15 to 30 seconds, then eat.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with flour.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in flour.
Add to mixture, then add coconut.
Cook in tube pan at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: real lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a heavy saucepan, combine 1 1/3 cups sugar and cornstarch; beat egg yolks and add to lemon mixture. Gradually add water, stirring constantly.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens, about 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add margarine; stir until melted.
Pour into prepared shell.

title: party punch
directions: Mix ingredients in a gallon jug. Add enough water to finish filling the jug up. Shake well. Place in freezer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon of peanut butter on each slice of bread. Then spread jelly evenly on one slice of bread. Place other slice of peanut butter and bread on top of each other. Cut sandwich.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery until tender.
Add rice.
Mix soups together and add to rice mixture.
Next, add 1 cup cheese, pimento, mushrooms and shredded chicken.
Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup cheese and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Shred lettuce and put in bottom of glass bowl.
Cook hamburger and taco mix according to directions.
Add on top of lettuce.
Toss on grated cheese.
Mash up Dorito chips and toss on top.
Serve like a tossed salad.
Sprinkle with taco sauce, tomatoes, and onions.
Serves 4.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Open beans and drain.
Mix with mushroom soup and fried onions.
Place in casserole dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese; place in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Mix together the rhubarb and sugar; boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove.
Mix in the jello.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in a little cold water; pour in boiling water. Put all other ingredients (except 1 box of Dream Whip, angel food cake, coconut and cherries).
Line a 4-quart bowl with foil or waxed paper.
Remove brown crust from cake; break in small pieces. Alternate cake with filling mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight or several hours.
Turn out on plate; frost with 1 package of Dream Whip and 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice.
Cover with coconut and cherries on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pickled okra
directions: Place garlic and hot pepper in bottom of clean jars. Leave part of stem on okra. Pack washed and drained okra tightly in jars, then add dill seed. Bring vinegar, water and salt to boiling; simmer 5 minutes. Pour over okra. Seal jars. Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes. Makes enough pickling solution for 4 pints.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and chill for 3 hours.
Roll into balls.
Optional to dip in chocolate.

title: basic waffle mix
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
In another bowl, mix yolks, melted butter and milk.
Add to dry ingredients. Beat the egg whites and fold into mix.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix together and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread and put, buttered side down in a 13 x 9 baking dish.
Brown sausage and drain grease.
Make it a crumbled texture.
Put on top of bread.
Cook hash browns as directed on package.
Layer on top of sausage.
Top with cheddar cheese. Scramble eggs in separate bowl and add milk, salt, and pepper. Pour evenly on top of casserole, cover with foil and refrigerate over night.
Take foil off and cook at 400 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.
You can vary the meat and the cheeses to your taste. Enjoy!!!!

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix instant pudding with orange juice, sour cream and milk; whisk until smooth (mixture will thicken).
Mix in fruit with a wooden spoon.
Cover and chill, then serve.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Brown chicken and onion in butter.
In a large pot, add celery, carrots, paprika, browned chicken and onion.
Cover with water.
Cook until done.
Keep at a boil.
Add dumplings.

title: jalapeno egg casserole
directions: Grate peppers and cheese; put in a pie plate.
Add eggs with a little milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil for 10 minutes before serving with crackers.

title: t v snack
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Cover. Seal for approximately 2 hours before serving. Stir to mix seasonings.

title: fruit fantastic
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix.
Chill.
Serves 10 or more.
Can be used as a salad, dessert or a topping for plain cake and for ice cream.

title: grampa's catfish stew
directions: In a large pot, cook the bacon until it is almost crisp.
Add the onions; saute until they are translucent.
Drain off the excess grease.
Add the tomato juice, tomato paste, catsup and garlic; cook, covered, over low heat for 2 1/2 hours.
Season with the salt and pepper, Tabasco and Worcestershire.
Add the catfish and the chopped eggs; cook over low heat for 30 minutes, breaking up the fish as it cooks.
Yields 8 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar and oil.
Pour over mixture in bowl, mix well.
Let cool and refrigerate overnight.

title: pork-pina hamonado
directions: Combine sugar, salt and praque powder or salitre.
Rub mixture on pork.
Spread pork and alternately arrange slices of pork fat, carrot, pickles and pineapple chunks until all ingredients are used up.
Roll and tie firmly with crocheting thread.
Combine dripping from pork, pineapple chunks syrup and pineapple juice then marinate meat overnight.
Simmer meat in marinade for 1 hour.
Remove thread from meat then chill if desired for ease of cutting.
Continue simmering the marinade for 5 minutes or until thick and serve as sauce.
Slice meat and arrange in a platter.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain pears and save juice.
Heat juice and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Put Jell-O and cream cheese in blender and blend.
Set in freezer to set.
While setting, cut up pears and chop nuts.
After Jell-O is somewhat set, whip the whipping cream.
Fold in pears, nuts and whipped cream.
Finish setting in refrigerator.

title: chicken breast lombardy
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper and flatten to 1/8-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Dredge chicken lightly with flour.
Place 4 pieces at a time in 2 tablespoons melted butter or margarine in a large skillet. Cook over low heat 3 or 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, overlapping edges.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Repeat procedure with remaining chicken, adding 2 tablespoons butter to skillet each time. Reserve drippings in skillet.
Saute mushrooms in 1/4 cup butter until tender; drain.
Sprinkle evenly over chicken.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix all; refrigerate.
Serve with crackers (Triscuits).

title: nine bean soup
directions: Soak and wash 2 cups bean mix.
Place in Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans and soak overnight.
Drain beans. Add 2 quarts water and next 3 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season to taste.

title: crunchy cole slaw
directions: In a bowl, mix toasted seeds, almonds and broken noodles; set aside.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients; gently roll into firm small balls 1 1/2 inches each.
Set aside.
Prepare sauce using chili sauce, cranberry sauce, sugar and lemon juice.
Place meatballs with sauce in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, mix sugar and flour well.
Add eggs, then milk, margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into two 9-inch pie pans or one deep dish pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until coconut browns on top and pie is set.

title: j.l.t. chili
directions: Pour oil into
14-inch Dutch oven and heat.
Add onions and cook
until
clear.
Add
meat,
bell
pepper and celery; thoroughly	brown.	When
done
skim or drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce
and
stir well.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add beans and chili powder and allow to simmer for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo and saute onion.
Mix cornbread mix, egg and corn. Pour into a 7 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish with butter and onion.
Top with sour cream.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Let set overnight or for a few hours.
Serve with pumpernickel bread, vegetables or chips.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Cut in butter with pastry cutter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Toss apples with water and lemon juice.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle flour mixture over apples and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: alaskan fireside coffee
directions: Boil until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Add juice of 6 lemons.

title: bloody mary mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
To make a pitcher full, just add 1 cup of vodka.
Serve over ice and garnish with celery sticks, if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and milk in a large bowl.
Add eggs and combine thoroughly.
Break meat into small pieces and combine with mixture, using a fork.
After all meat is added, work with hands to combine thoroughly.
Form loaf in shallow baking dish, 1-inch larger than loaf on all sides.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Pour off excess liquid and let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: seasoning shaker
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 1/3 cup.
Use this in place of your regular table salt.

title: linguine salad with sesame dressing
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients and pour 1/2 on linguine and let set for 3-8 hrs.
Mix 1 cup chopped cilantro with rest of dressing and mix into linguine prior to serving.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: white fruit cake - old kentucky recipe
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Remove one cup of flour and sift it over fruit and nut mixture.
Set aside.
Sift together remaining flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Cream butter and sugar; add flour mixture, then the fruits and nuts.
Separate the eggs, beating the egg whites until stiff.
Fold the egg whites into the rest of cake batter.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours in three 10 3/4 x 4 1/4 x 2 1/2-inch deep pans.
Lightly grease pans, bottom and sides, then cut a piece of wax paper to fit bottom of pans and grease it also.

title: baby back ribs with oyster sauce
directions: Peel garlic cloves and smash them.
Peel ginger root and smash them.
Put ribs in a pot on top of the stove, covered with garlic and ginger.
Turn heat on medium-high; cook for 45 minutes. Uncover and pour oyster sauce over ribs.
Mix water in oyster sauce bottle 1/2 full.
Shake well and pour over ribs.
Cover and continue to cook at medium heat for 15 minutes.
Uncover, add 1 cup sugar, mixing well.
Cover and continue to cook for 15 minutes.
Uncover and turn off heat.
Allow ribs to air cook.
Eat 'em up.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Combine ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Serve on crisp lettuce. Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Melt butter and blend with flour.
Add milk, water and salt. Cook until thickened.
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg yolks. Add salmon.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Place in pan of hot water and bake (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Lightly brown ground beef, onion, chili powder, salt and sugar.
Stir and mix well.
Add beans, soup and juice. Stir and simmer 1 hour.
Tastes better next day.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cut into small squares.
Serve warm.

title: sesame spinach
directions: Mix the soy sauce, sesame oil and sugar.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Quickly stir-fry the garlic, ginger and scallions.
Add the spinach and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the soy sauce mix and heat through. Serve immediately.

title: baked chicken (or turkey) and broccoli dish
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to directions.
Stir in 1/2 cup French fried onions. Spread stuffing mix over greased 9-inch dish. Arrange broccoli spear flowerets on outer edge. Prepare cheese sauce according to directions.
Using 1 1/4 cups milk, stir in sour cream. Combine chicken or turkey with cheese, milk and sour cream mixture.
Pour over broccoli and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining French fried onions over top. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add juice.
Stir in sherbet and oranges sliced in half.
Chill until firm.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar 5 minutes.
Add lemon and pumpkin.
Sift together the six dry ingredients and fold in egg mixture.
Put in greased and floured 10 x 15 inch pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 15 minutes.
Invert cake onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar, roll in cloth and cool.
To make filling, mix last four ingredients together, beating well.
Unroll cooled cake, spread with filling and reroll.
Chill.

title: pecan-cheesecake squares(microwave)
directions: Microwave (High) the butter in uncovered glass mixing bowl for 20 to 30 seconds or until softened.
Blend in brown sugar until creamy.
Mix in flour with fork until crumbly.
Stir in pecans. Set aside 1/2 cup mixture.
Press remainder into bottom of 8-inch square microwave-safe dish.
Microwave (High), uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until mixture is puffed and has a dry appearance, rotating dish once.
Set aside.
Microwave (High) the remaining crumb mixture in uncovered dish for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until lightly toasted, stirring once or twice.
Set aside.

title: fluffy cottage cheese blintzes
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add cottage cheese; beat until almost smooth.
Blend in skim milk, flour and salt.
Beat egg whites until peaks fold over. Fold into batter.
Let batter stand 5 minutes.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter onto a preheated griddle which has been brushed lightly with oil.
Bake until the top is bubbly and edges are baked.
Turn and bake the other side.
Serve at once with mock sour cream or fruit.
Yields 6 small Blintzes.
Each serving contains approximately 55 calories.

title: fluffy biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In medium bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor fashion, cut in margarine or butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, stir in milk just until blended.
Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of mixture 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: green grape salad
directions: Mix together, chill and serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Dump all together and cook uncovered 3 hours.
Add just enough water to rinse cans.

title: rita's goulash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook macaroni.
Add all ingredients together and cook for 3 hours on low heat.

title: hamburger-bean casserolediagonal, iowa
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and pour off grease.

title: steak surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute steak and onions in 1 tablespoon of butter until lightly browned.
Add liquid from mushrooms, bay leaf and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover, simmer gently 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Combine steak with pan juices, mushrooms, soup, noodles, remaining butter, milk, water, salt and pepper.
Put in 1 1/2-quart wide and shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve about 3,800 people.
Add rabbits only if more than expected come, as most people do not like hare in their stew!

title: catfish soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fish, in a 6-quart pot or Dutch oven.
Bring to boil over high heat. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes until potatoes are tender. Add catfish and simmer, stirring occasionally for 12 to 15 minutes until catfish begins to flake.

title: christmas tree bread
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and yeast in large bowl. Melt butter; add milk and eggs.
Mix together and add to flour mixture.
Mix, then spread out on greased cookie sheet with sides or 9 x 13-inch cake pan; pour butter (1/3 cup), brown sugar and nuts over dough.
Shape into a tree or a log.
Slit the top open and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour in tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 350° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine and shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in oven 12 minutes at 500°.

title: ginger chicken and beans
directions: Cut chicken breasts in halves; coat with flour.
Cook chicken in oil in skillet or Dutch oven until brown on all sides; remove from skillet.
Drain excess fat from skillet.
Add onions, pepper, ginger and garlic and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in 1 tablespoon flour, spices and pepper; saute until onions are tender, 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: In a 9 x 13 microwave dish, layer cream cheese, then chili. Sprinkle on peppers, then cheese.
Zap in microwave until cheese is melted and chili is warm.
Serve warm with your favorite chips.

title: tomato and cauliflower salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and salt in hot water.
Add cold water, vinegar and pepper.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in vegetables.
Pour into molds or dish. Chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens.
Serve with salad dressing or mayo.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring 1-quart water to a boil, add 1/2 cup diced potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.
After lowering heat to medium, add other 2 cups of potatoes, celery and onions.
Cook until nearly tender; add carrots and cook 5 minutes.
Add milk and stir over low heat until heated through.
Add margarine and serve immediately.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: You will need a deep fryer with oil.

title: cookies and cream dessert
directions: In one bowl, combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter. Mix by hand or by mixer.
(Recommended by mixer.)
In another large bowl, combine vanilla pudding and milk.
In larger bowl, combine ingredients from both bowls.
Using mixer, fold in Cool Whip. Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with half of crushed Oreos.
Pour in pudding mixture.
Top with rest of Oreos.
Place in refrigerator.
Let set for 3 to 4 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding and milk.
Mix mixtures together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Use a plastic flower pot.
Layer cookie crumbs, mixture, crumbs and mixture.
Add gummy worms on top.
Refrigerate.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Lightly brown hamburger.
Add onions and cook until tender but not brown.
Add corn, soups, sour cream, pimento, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add noodles.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter 13 x 9-inch or 2 (8-inch) square dish.
In skillet, saute onion, set aside.
Mix eggs and milk until blended.
Add corn and muffin mix.
Mix well.
Spread corn bread batter into baking dish.
Spoon sauteed onion over top.
Spread sour cream over mix.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 35 minutes until puffed and golden.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
May be refrigerated or frozen and reheated.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and vanilla. Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set but not brown.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Roll in sugar again.

title: chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake the cake in a 10 x 15 x 2-inch baking pan according to box directions.
Check for firmness in about 30 minutes.
While cake is baking, beat together cream cheese, sour cream, milk and pudding.
Beat until mixture is quite thick, 4 to 7 minutes.
Cool cake at least 2 hours after baking.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir milk and egg and add small amount of boiling water to this and set aside. Mix dry ingredients, pepper and onion and add liquid ingredients.
Spoon into hot oil, using one spoon to dip and second to rake off.
Cook until lightly browned.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet with ready to bake crescent dough.
Bake until golden brown (about 10 minutes). Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, dressing mix, Miracle Whip and sour cream.
Spread over baked crust.
Top with assorted chopped vegetables of your choice.

title: chicken eugene
directions: Preheat oven to 250 degrees. Spray 9 x 13 inch baking dish with non stick cooking spray. Tear chipped beef and place in bottom of pan. Take bacon strips and wrap around each piece of chicken. Place in dish. Mix mushroom soup and sour cream together in mixing bowl and pour over chicken. Bake for 2 hours. Serve with mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: ice cream punch
directions: In nonmetal container, combine water and concentrates.
In punch bowl, place sherbet and ice cream; break into small pieces with large spoon.
Add liquid mixture; stir until sherbet and ice cream are partially melted.
Serves 40 (1/2 cup).

title: pasta and cheese salad(with herbed yogurt dressing)
directions: Cook and drain pasta according to package directions.
Place in a large bowl with Cheddar cheese, peas and celery.
In a small bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise, mustard, dill, salt and black pepper.
Pour over pasta mixture, stirring until evenly coated. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add tomatoes just before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch or six 3 x 7 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Mix sugar and Crisco well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in bananas and buttermilk.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into loaf pans of your choice.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: vals mock sour cream
directions: Process in blender until smooth and creamy.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Chill pastry shell.
Chop shrimp (cut in half).
Toss cheese with the flour and set aside.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Spread 3/4 cheese mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Next, layer in shrimp and cover with rest of cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 40 minutes or until set.
Let set 10 minutes and then cut and enjoy.

title: corn mushroom casserole
directions: Mix drained corn and beaten eggs in a buttered 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Drain mushrooms, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Stir in drained mushrooms and salts.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top. Dot with butter and add reserved mushroom liquid to milk and pour over crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Cook together when beef is tender.
Add noodles.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Chill well; form into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter with sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir together flour, soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture to make smooth dough.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place in ungreased miniature muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Have mini peanut butter cups ready, papers removed.

title: dutch babies
directions: Put margarine into a 9 x 13-inch pan and melt in a 425° oven. Put eggs
into
a blender and mix on high for 1 minute. Keep blender running and add milk and flour.
Pour batter into hot pan and return to oven.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: nitey night cookies
directions: You can use just pecans and not chips.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Sprinkle broccoli, cheese and onion on pie crusts.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crusts. Cook, uncovered, at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300°; cook for about 30 minutes, until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: country potato soup
directions: In a deep pan, over a medium heat, saute the bacon, celery and onion until the onion is golden brown, about 5 minutes.

Add the potatoes, water and seasonings, raise the heat to high and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cover, simmer for 15 minutes or until the potatoes are tender. Mash the potatoes slightly, about 1/4 of the cubes should be left whole. Remove the bay leaf, add the milk, Worcestershire sauce and parsley and bring back to a boil. Serves 4-6.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add egg, then dry ingredients alternately with hot water and molasses.
Bake in greased pan in 350° oven.

title: scrumptious blueberry muffins(low-fat)
directions: Into the cake mix, add the eggs, water and oil; blend well. Stir in softened cream cheese.
Fold in the blueberries and pecans.

title: marinated fresh vegetable salad
directions: Place vegetables in large plastic container.
Combine liquid ingredients in a separate container; mix well and pour over vegetables.
Seal and chill overnight.
Makes a tangy, colorful dish low in calories.

title: basil & tomato risotto
directions: Cook onion and garlic in butter in large skillet over medium high heat until soft.
Add rice and stir three (3) minutes.
Add wine, stir until absorbed.
Stir in one (1) cup of broth; cook uncovered stirring constantly until broth is absorbed.
Continue stirring adding broth and water one (1) cup at a time.
Each cup should absorb before adding another, until rice is tender and has creamy consistency (25 minutes).
Stir in tomatoes, basil, cheese, pepper and cream.
Stir until creamy (1 to 2 minutes).
Serve immediately.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar and oil; add eggs.
Blend in flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add nuts, apples, vanilla and coconut.
Put in greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: corn topped meat squares
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, ketchup, onion, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Pat the mixture evenly in a 9-inch baking pan. Combine egg, milk and corn.
Pour over meat.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake another 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until fluffy in large mixing bowl; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Roll dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Cut with floured cookie cutters.
Place cookies on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle sugar on top while hot.

title: bread stuffing(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Combine water, onion and celery in a saucepan.
Mix well. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss with a fork until well mixed.
Do not stuff turkey until you are ready to roast it, then spoon stuffing lightly into turkey.
Do not pack tightly.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour all ingredients in bowl and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Crust:
Combine flour, 2/3 cup cheese, almonds, salt and paprika.
Stir in oil.
Set aside 1/2 cup mixture.
Press remaining mix into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove and reduce heat to 325°.

title: yeast bread
directions: Heat water to 115°.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Pour in bowl and add oil, sugar and salt.
Beat with dough hooks until mixed well.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until well mixed.
Then add additional flour until a soft ball is formed.
Beat about 8 minutes.
Dough can be mixed in food processor or by hand.
Put 1/4 teaspoon oil in bowls and divide dough and roll in oil and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake in round pan or loaf pans.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and soda; gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing until blended.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Spoon half of batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with blueberries, 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Let cool completely on a wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: belle's famous spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package label.
Place spaghetti in strainer.
Rinse with warm to cold water and drain.
Slightly cover entire bottom of 10-inch skillet with salt, place layer of finely chopped onion and bell pepper over salt.
Cover these ingredients with ground beef, topped with a generous amount of chili powder.
Cook on low heat until beef begins to change color (approximately 12 minutes).
Chop and stir until beef is thoroughly cooked.
Dilute sauce with water and mix into spaghetti.
Add more salt, chili powder, sugar and red pepper (if desired) to taste.
Cover and simmer from 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: mexican enchiladas
directions: Combine 3/4 cup of flour with next 4 ingredients and a pinch of salt in small bowl, beating thoroughly.
Let stand for 1 hour. Spoon 2 tablespoons of batter into hot 6-inch skillet, tilting to coat bottom.
Cook until slightly brown; turn and cook for several seconds longer.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add other ingredients and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: day ahead cake
directions: Mix margarine, egg and sugar.
Add strawberries.
Fold in nuts and Cool Whip.
Place layer of wafers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread half of mixture over wafers.
Add another layer of wafers and put rest of mixture on top.
Refrigerate.

title: spaghetti sicilian style
directions: Heat olive oil in a skillet.
Stir in garlic.
Remove garlic from oil when brown.
Stir eggplant and tomatoes into skillet; simmer for 30 minutes.
Cut peppers vertically in half.
Remove membranes and seeds.
Place peppers under broiler, skin side up, to loosen skin.
Peel off skin.
Slice peppers and add to tomato mixture.
Stir basil, capers, anchovies, olives, salt and pepper into tomato mixture.
Cover the skillet and simmer 10 minutes or until sauce is well blended and thickened.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain.
Immediately pour sauce over spaghetti and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: molasses sugar cookies(yields 12 servings)
directions: Combine flour, sugar, molasses, milk, egg and spices. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Make into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves, ginger, and nutmeg.
Pour pumpkin mixture in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle one box of yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Gently pat cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Drizzle butter evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mystery fruit cake balls
directions: Prepare and bake cake as directed. Cool. Prepare frosting mix as directed. Crumble cooled cake into large bowl. Add nuts, fruit and frosting. Toss together until mixture is damp and well blended. Shape in 1-inch balls with buttered hands. Chill in refrigerator for 24 hours. Roll in powdered sugar or leave plain.

title: creamy white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, corn syrup, salt and butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Cover and cook slowly 5 minutes.
Uncover and boil rapidly to soft ball stage 236° on candy thermometer.
Let stand until cold; add vanilla and beat until candy loses its gloss and begins to hold shape.
Stir in walnuts and turn into an oiled pan.
Cut in squares when set.
Makes 2 1/4 pounds.

title: chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Thoroughly combine first 5 ingredients with water.
Heat oil in wok or skillet over high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add vegetables and golden onion recipe soup mixture. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes or until thickened.
Serve over hot rice.

title: banana crunch cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan. Mix butter. Add frosting mix and oatmeal. Set aside. Mix sour cream, bananas and eggs in mixer. Add cake mix and blend. Alternate cake mix with crumb mix, ending with crumb mix. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Let cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Drain most of the liquid off the mixed vegetables.
Add cheese and mix well.
Pour in a casserole dish. Crumble 1 package Hi Ho crackers on top of vegetables.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise 1/4 teaspoon curry and artichoke liquid.
Mix with other ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Best served next day.

title: grandmother's 12-hour beef stew
directions: Season meat.
Place in bottom of slow cooker.
Sprinkle with tapioca.
Arrange layer of onion, potato, carrots and celery. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: orange delight cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs; add vanilla and orange rinds.
Add sour milk and soda.
Alternating with dry ingredients while still warm, spoon topping over each cookie.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: florida punch
directions: Mix water, orange juice and lemonade. Dollop with ice cream and sherbet.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: First mix cake mix, nuts, 1 egg and melted oleo.
Press into 9 x
13-inch
pan.
Second
mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour
over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin-nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 24 muffin-pan cups or line with paper baking cups.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whipped cream frosting(not too sweet)
directions: Combine milk or half and half and flour in a shaker.
Shake until smooth.
Pour into small saucepan.
Stir on medium heat until thick.
Lay a piece of wax paper on top to prevent skin from forming.
Let cool.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter in saucepan until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat and simmer. Use for beef, chicken or pork.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend flour and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Beat well.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: sis. mclain's  strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie shells. Combine 1 cup water with strawberry jello and 1/2 cup water with cornstarch.
Add sugar. Cook until slightly thickened. Cool mixture in refrigerator.
Pour over strawberries in pie shells. Top with Cool Whip.

title: homemade picante sauce
directions: In blender or food processor, chop vegetables.
Add juice from the tomatoes, then add canned tomatoes.
Add spices and refrigerate.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Cream together the sugar and Crisco.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour and baking powder.
Reserve 1/2 cup of dough.
Spread remaining dough on cookie sheet or pizza pan. Cover with pie filling; dot with the dough you reserved.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, until crust is golden and topping bubbles.
Cut in squares to serve.
Makes approximately 36 squares.

title: baked corn with sour cream and jack cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch quiche dish or 6 cup shallow baking dish.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple and fruit cocktail in 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Spread dry cake mix over pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Slice thin pats of butter over entire cake and bake at 350° until brown. Serve while hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: equal candy bar
directions: Mix ingredients with fork or hands.
Shape into 2 small rolls. Roll in chopped pecans.
Place on wax paper.
Chill until firm. Makes 2 servings, 165 calories each.

title: russian tea
directions: Make 2 gallons tea in the usual way.
Sweeten to taste.
Add the strained juice of 1 dozen oranges and 1 dozen lemons.
Tie 1 tablespoon cinnamon bark in a thin cloth.
Boil all together 5 minutes.
Serve hot, putting 2 cloves in each cup.

title: microwave pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers in food processor.
Mix in with sugar and vinegar in an 8-cup measure.
Microwave on High until mixture boils (about 10 to 12 minutes).
Stir.
Microwave on 2/3 power (or Medium) for 5 minutes.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes.
Add Certo.
Microwave on High until mixture comes to a boil (about 5 minutes).
Remove and add enough green food coloring to make a pretty green.
Pour in sterilized jelly jars.
Seal with lids and rings or paraffin.
Cool completely before storing.
Makes 6 to 8 jelly jars.

title: easter nests
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat marshmallow cream, peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Fold in noodles and plain M&M's.
Chill until easy to handle.
On wax paper form mixture by 1/3 cup into 3-inch nests.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Place several peanut M&M's in each nest. Yields 9 servings.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and margarine.
Add flour and beat well.
Form into marble size balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Spread in a large casserole dish.
Mix soups together; rinse cans with small amount water and heat.
Spread over ground beef.
Grate cheese; spread over soups. Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cover the cucumber, tomato and onion with Kraft Italian dressing (no fat) overnight.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Chop celery
and
onion.
Slice eggs and crumble bacon. Layer in bowl as listed.	Spread Parmesan cheese on top.

title: applesauce bars or no eggs cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine with sugar. Add applesauce and the rest of ingredients. Put in Bundt pan or 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or so.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla and sweetened condensed milk at slow speed.
Then add chunky peanut butter into mixture, mixing with a spoon.
Put in ice cream freezer.
Add whole milk to fill freezer to the proper fullness for freezing.
Make ice cream according to your freezer's directions.

title: picante sauce
directions: Heat tomatoes, peel and core.
Add tomatoes to ingredients. Cook in a large pan until sauce has cooked down to 1/2 its size.

title: ultimate dessert
directions: Spray a rectangular casserole dish with cooking spray. Drain peaches and place them into dish (you may also use apples, blackberries or strawberries instead of peaches). Cut peaches into smaller pieces. Pour Duncan Hines yellow cake mix over the top of peaches. Level and smooth mix with a spoon. Melt butter and drizzle over top of peaches and cake mix. Spray the top with cooking spray especially in areas that were not covered in butter. Bake in oven at 375° for about 45 to 60 minutes, until the top is nice and brown.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread over the flank steak early in the day.
Refrigerate, covered, until ready to broil or grill. For best results, only cook steak to the medium stage.
Slice the steak thinly on the bias.

title: pea pickin cake
directions: Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake as directed on box.

title: quick chicken
directions: Heat olive oil in Dutch oven.
Place chicken in oil and brown. Mix water and bouillon and pour over chicken.
Add potatoes, placing around chicken.
Sprinkle onion, garlic and lemon pepper over chicken and potatoes.
Cover and bring to a light boil. Reduce heat to low and cook for 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings; 5 grams fat each.

title: rice waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks, beaten with the milk. Beat until smooth.
Add rice and melted butter.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake on hot waffle iron.
Serve at once. Yield:
4 waffles.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix zucchini with salt in colander.
Let drain for 1/2 hour. Squeeze out excess liquid.
Mix zucchini with carrots, onion, parsley, egg, flour and pepper.
Drop by tablespoonfuls in 1/2-inch hot oil.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown onions in bacon fat until golden.
Remove onions and brown pork, cut in small cubes, in same pot.
Drain excess fat. Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Put onions back with pork; pour hot water over mixture and cook covered, in 300° oven for about 45 minutes or until pork is fork-tender.
Add sauerkraut which has been simmered until strands are tender.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Serve with boiled potatoes, buttered and sprinkled with caraway seed, dark pumpernickel bread and Liederkranz cheese and beer or ale.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil.
Coat chicken with flour and salt.
Cook chicken in oil 15 to 20 minutes on all sides.
Add green pepper and onions. Saute 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti. Serves 4.

title: onion cold mix
directions: Roast an onion wrapped in a wet cloth on hot ashes until soft. Peel the outside off and mash them.
Apply on a cloth to the hollow of the feet.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add the raspberries and stir until thawed.
Add sliced bananas, crushed pineapple and nuts. Spread half of mixture in pan or dish, 8 x 15-inch, and chill 1 1/2 hours.
Spread sour cream over chilled Jell-O mixture, then spread remaining Jell-O mixture over top and chill until set.

title: chicken cheese puff
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice for a beverage.
Blend pineapple, eggs, cheese, chicken, chilies, flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Coat bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan with margarine.
Pour chicken mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake
in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted near middle comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients. Add remaining, one at a time.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: my sister marilyn's sauerkraut balls(tastes like eggrolls.)
directions: Cook sausage & onion; add snipped sauerkraut & crumbs.
Mix the ingredients listed from cream cheese to pepper & then in with meat/kraut.
Set in fridge to harden, then shape into 1 1/2 inch balls.
In a small bowl, mix the eggs and milk.
Roll balls in flour, egg mixture & crumbs & deep fry until crisp. Bake at 375 - 15-20 minutes.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: beef and macaroni dish
directions: Brown beef in electric frying pan.
Add chopped onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, catsup and drained macaroni. Let simmer until done.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix and keep chilled until served.
This is delicious! Leftovers?
Use on wedges of lettuce as a dressing.

title: crawfish etouffee(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and butter until browned. Add cream of mushroom soup with cream cheese; let cook down for approximately 1 hour. Add seasonings; add seafood with cognac. Cook for 20 minutes on low fire. Add onion tops and stir until well mixed. Serve over rice, hot.

title: sparkling strawberry punch
directions: Combine the sugar and 1/2 cup water in saucepan.
Cook and stir until the sugar is dissolved, boiling for 3 minutes. Refrigerate. Combine sugar syrup, daiquiri mix (undiluted), limeade (undiluted), strawberries and
the ice water in a punch bowl.
Add ice.
Pour in the sparkling water.

title: zucchini cheese omelet
directions: Slice zucchini in thin slices.
Set aside.
Lightly brown onion in bacon grease after the bacon is done.
Pour off some excess fat and add sliced zucchini and butter.
Cover loosely and steam about 5 minutes.
Stir several times.
Beat eggs and season. Add grated cheese.
Mix well and pour into skillet with other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat; turn.
Brown lightly on other side.
Serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: italian chicken
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and any extra seasoning in small bowl.
Dip chicken in butter.
Then roll in crumb mixture.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350° in a flat pan, uncovered.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well the eggs, sugar, oil and zucchini.
Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and nutmeg; add this to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Add the vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread and greens
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl stir together dry ingredients.
Add oil and boiling water.
Stir well.
Add buttermilk and eggs, stirring until smooth.
Stir in an additional 1 to 2 T. buttermilk if batter seems too thick.
Place butter in an 8x8x2 in baking pan or a large cast iron skillet.
Heat in oven just until butter melts.
Spread cornmeal batter in pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to 375° and bake for 20-25 minutes more until lightly golden and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into squares,
Serve warm with butter and honey or homemade preserves.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook sausage in saucepan for about 30 minutes.
Put it through a blender, chopping it fine.
Add cheese, onions, bread crumbs, butter, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Wash mushrooms, break off stems and chop stems to add to mixture.
Fill mushrooms and place in a baking dish with a little water.
Cook for 20 minutes or until tender.
Bake at 350°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over the baked pretzels. Spread cherry pie filling on top.

title: fruit salsa
directions: Dice up fruit very small.
Add sugar to sweeten.
Squeeze juice over top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Take off bone and cut in small pieces.
Put in dish.
Mix soup, dip and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers over mixture.
Dot butter on top of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate powder mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 3 teaspoons mix to 1/2 cup boiling water.
If desired, add marshmallows.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix by hand until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 12-cup tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan. Remove from pan.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugar; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill until firm.
Roll with your hands, small amounts of the dough, the size of your finger; cut each 1 1/2-inches or 2-inches and shape into crescents.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until golden brown on the bottom.
Check after 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when they are cool enough to handle.

title: southern pudding
directions: Chop carrots and shred sweet potatoes.
Combine vegetables, melted lard and sugar.
Sift together the flour, spices, salt and soda and add to the other mixture.
Add raisins and pour into a well-greased quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours in a slow oven (300°).

title: almond-filled strudel
directions: In a small bowl, beat sugar and butter until creamy.
Beat in egg, almonds, almond extract and rum.
Cover and chill 30 to 45 minutes or until very cold and stiff.
Thaw pastry 20 minutes; unfold and roll on a lightly floured surface to a 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Transfer to a large ungreased baking sheet.
Spoon almond filling lengthwise down center third of pastry.
Brush edges with egg-water mixture.
Fold pastry on left side of filling over filling; fold pastry on right side of filling over the enclosed filling completely.
Pinch edges to seal.
Turn filled pastry over so folded edges are down; seal ends by pressing with the tines of a fork.
Brush top with egg-water mixture; refrigerate 30 minutes. Heat oven to 425°.
Using a sharp knife, score top of pastry several times, being careful not to cut through pastry.
Bake 30 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Cool on wire rack for several hours before serving.
Serves 8.

title: poor-man steak
directions: Mix beef, salt, pepper, onion and 1 teaspoon gravy mix.
Pat in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix soup with 1/2 teaspoon gravy mix and spread on top of meat.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Scald 1 1/2 cups of the milk in medium saucepan.
Combine the cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt in a small bowl.
Blend remaining 1/2 cup cold milk into cocoa mixture.
Mix well.
Stir into scalded milk.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool.
Spoon into 4 individual dessert dishes and refrigerate.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place dry milk in blender; add sugar and boiling water.
Blend until smooth.

title: cheese crunchers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Over hot water, melt morsels and butter, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Transfer to large bowl; stir in graham cracker crumbs and nuts with fork until crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups crumbly mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan (9 x 13-inch works okay). Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Using beater, cream butter and sugar.
Add almonds, flour, salt and extract.
Mix with hands into small balls.
Roll enough to make dough stick together.
Line
a cookie sheet with foil. Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until light brown.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: mother's economy raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins and water down to 1 cup of juice.
Strain and add soda to the juice.
Cool slightly and add shortening and sugar to the warm liquid.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon together 3 times and to other mixture.
Mix well.
Add raisins.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan or iron skillet, for about 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp and cheese dip
directions: Rinse shrimp well and drain.
Mix shrimp, shredded cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Miracle Whip.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, lemon rind, spices and salt together. Sprinkle a little on the bottom of a nine inch unbaked pie crust. Arrange tomatoes in pie shell, one layer at a time. Cover each layer with sugar mixture, lemon juice and dot with butter. Cover with latticed top, or a regular top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: old fashioned fruit cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream eggs, butter, sugar and milk.
Combine with dry mixture; mix well.
Pour hot water over raisins; let stand a few minutes, then drain.
Cut dates and figs in small pieces; add a little flour to prevent sticking.
Add jam, nuts and fruit to cake mixture.
Bake in 4 layers at 300° for 1 hour.
