title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and beans.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well. Spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers and spread over top.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Freezes well.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all together in saucepan.
Cook until mixture forms a ball.
Store in refrigerator.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: For pork chop preparation, request butcher to cut a gash or pocket into the side of each chop.
Salt and pepper chops well.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in a casserole dish.

title: toasted onion soup
directions: Slice onions, then saute in butter until transparent.
Stir in flour and simmer 2 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, wine and cheese.
Bake at 250° for 3 to 8 hours.
Stir occasionally.
The longer it bakes, the browner it gets.
Beef broth may be used instead of chicken.
Don't salt until you taste.

title: sesame sauce
directions: In a small pan heated with coat of oil, brown onion.
Add water.
Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes on low heat.
Thin tahini with water.
Add to onions.
Stir in soy sauce. Bring to boil.
Add wine.
Stir and take off heat.
Good with rice or steamed veggies.

title: secret homemade bread
directions: Pour half of butter into tube cake pan.
Place biscuits in pan in 2 layers, overlapping biscuits on the first and second layers. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Pour remaining half of butter over top when it has finished baking.

title: shapiro's stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and blanch in a large pot of boiling water until leaves begin to loosen.
Soak bread in red wine.
Combine ground chuck, onion, celery and egg.
Mix in wet bread (bare hands are the best tools for this).
Add tomato juice, rice, salt and pepper.
Carefully peel off cabbage leaves and roll each around 1 to 2 tablespoons of the meat mixture, tucking in the sides so it holds together.
Repeat until all the beef is wrapped.
There should be 18 to 20 packets.
Chop remaining cabbage leaves and reserve 4 cups.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces almond bark in large saucepan over low heat.
Stir until smooth and remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken breasts in oleo; roll in crumb mixture.
Place in greased dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then stir in pulp, milk and beaten egg. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve cold.

title: pepperoni loaf
directions: On a floured surface, roll dough out thin.
Beat egg and add oregano and garlic powder.
Spread on dough (you don't have to use it all).
Place Provolone on dough.
Add pepperoni on top, overlapping.
Sprinkle with a little oregano.
Put Mozzarella on top.
Roll in log fashion.
You may use toothpicks to hold together.
Place on an oiled cookie sheet.
Put a little oil on surface.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Serve with pizza sauce.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Set aside about 8 strawberry slices for garnish.
Combine remaining strawberries and sugar; chill.
Prepare pudding:
Mix according to package directions; set aside.
Layer 1/3 each of cake, strawberries, and pudding in a 3 quart glass bowl.
Repeat layers twice, ending with pudding.
Spread whipped topping over trifle and garnish with strawberries.
Chill. Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: calico bean dip
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Brown hamburger and onions.
Partially drain kidney and butter beans.
Mix all together in a large baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: meatball sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and dissolve sugar.
Pour over meatballs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked bluefish
directions: Garlic and wine take away the strong fish taste.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in shallow baking dish.
Place fillets sprinkled with chopped garlic, parsley, pepper and lemon juice.
Cover with seasoned bread crumbs and pour 1/4 cup melted butter over it. Wine may be added before crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Spread pecans on bottom of a 6 x 10-inch pan.
Boil butter and brown sugar for 7 minutes.
Pour over nuts.
Sprinkle chocolate over top and cover until melted.
Cool and break into squares.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Make hot roll mix as directed.
Spread on jelly roll pan. Then place ingredients in order listed and bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain on paper towels.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 2 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator overnight covered with foil.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: picante-hamburger dip
directions: Melt all together and serve with chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with onion; drain.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise, mushroom soup and cheese.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.
(I only use 1 package frozen broccoli.)

title: hershey bar pie
directions: In top of double boiler, melt Hershey bar, milk and marshmallows.
Cool.
Whip the cream in bowl until stiff and fold this into chocolate mixture.
Pour into crust and place in refrigerator to cool.
When cool, place in freezer.
Remove at dinnertime and pie will be thawed for dessert.
Keeps indefinitely in freezer.

title: quick brownies with frosting
directions: Combine water, cocoa and margarine; bring to a boil. Remove from heat. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking soda. In a small bowl, beat milk and eggs. Take flour mixture and milk mixture and blend. Add cocoa mixture (still warm); beat all ingredients together until lumps are gone. Grease an 11 x 16 1/2-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: dip for chips
directions: Heat the beans, cheese and peppers in microwave oven. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and crushed potato chips.
Use as dip for chips.
The firmer ones work best.
Also try tortilla chips.

title: icebox pudding
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and egg, beat well.
Add milk or cream, nuts, pineapple, vanilla and stir well.
Fold in 1/2 pint whipped cream.
Roll 2/3 pound of vanilla wafers.
Sprinkle 1/2 crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and pour the mixture over crumbs. Then sprinkle the other half of crumbs over the second layer.
Set in refrigerator until chilled.
Can be made several hours in advance.
Serve with nuts or cherries on top.

title: apple breakfast bake
directions: Spread butter on bottom and sides of 9 x 9-inch pan or 9 x 13-inch for double recipe.
Cut apples in pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top.
Combine eggs, milk, flour and salt until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Butter 9-inch pie plate.
Layer cranberries on bottom of pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
In a bowl, beat egg until thick. Gradually add sugar, beating until thoroughly blended.
Stir in flour and melted margarine.
Blend well.
Pour over cranberries and bake 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine milk and shortening in saucepan over medium to low heat until melted.
Pour into large bowl; cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water and stir into milk mixture.
Add sugar and salt; stir until dissolved.
Add sifted flour, beating until smooth and until dough pulls away from spoon. Cover with plate and let rise overnight in refrigerator.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Mix together dry mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Let stand 2 hours.
Beat eggs until frothy and add to mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick, about 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Add beer.

title: chicken francaise
directions: Dip chicken in flour. Then coat with egg.
Saute chicken in butter and remove.
Add wine and lemon juice to deglaze pan and pour over chicken (can be added with chicken in pan).
If you like more sauce, increase sherry and lemon juice mixture in 2 to 1 ratio.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first sugar and flour.
Drop in egg yolks and cocoa. Slowly add cold milk.
Cook on top of stove until thick.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat, then add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with margarine and put back in oven until golden brown.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Combine turkey with all remaining ingredients.
Form into a loaf and place in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in large salad bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and cheese.
Spread over other ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolk; mix well. Stir in flour by hand on lightly floured surface gently.

Knead dough 2 to 3 minutes until thoroughly combined. Roll into 1-inch balls. Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Make indention with thumb in center of each; fill with 1/4 teaspoon preserves.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: baked sauerkraut
directions: Simmer onion in oil until brown.
Stir in catsup, water, sugar and mustard.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream sugar with margarine; beat eggs and add.
Sift all dry ingredients and add alternately with the milk.
Stir in the berries with a little flour.
Grease muffin pans.
Pour batter in; makes 1 dozen.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, cook sausage over medium heat, stirring frequently until no longer pink.
Separate rolls into eight triangles.
Place in ungreased 12-inch rimmed pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press together, seal perforations and form a circle 1-inch larger in diameter than pan bottom.
Turn edges under to make a slight rim.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over crust.
Top with potatoes, peppers, onions and cheese.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Blend together butter, flour, salt, paprika and curry powder. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Stir constantly.

Add ketchup, sherry and shrimp; heat thoroughly. Serve over rice with condiments such as Indian relish, chopped nuts, raisins, hard-boiled egg whites and yolks, shredded coconut and Major Grey's chutney.
Serves 6.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a piece of bacon.
Cover bottom of flat, greased baking dish with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken breasts on top.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Can be made day before and refrigerated overnight.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers; sprinkle with salt.
Stir and let set for 1 hour.
Drain; slice onions and mix with cucumbers.
Pack in containers.
Cover with first mixtures; then freeze.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be thick, so mix with
hands, if necessary.	Press firmly into 2 loaf pans, lined with
waxed paper.	Refrigerate until ready to slice and serve.

title: mom's vegetable soup
directions: Use 4-quart pot.
Brown beef tips on high, stirring constantly, until they are light brown.
Remove from heat.
Add hot water until the pan is a little over half full.
Add rest of ingredients except onion soup mix, then add more water to fill the pan about 3 inches from top.
Bring to boil and then add onion soup mix.
Turn heat to low and cover.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours. May also be cooked in crock-pot for several hours.

title: orange bavarian cream
directions: Beat yogurt and pudding mix (dry) in a medium bowl on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat in whipping cream on medium speed 3 to 5 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally until soft peaks form. Garnish with Mandarin orange segments.
Refrigerate.
Serves 4 to 6, 320 calories per serving.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in food processor.
Cream butter, cheese and sugar. In separate bowl, mix pudding and milk until well blended.
Then blend in Cool Whip.
Add this to cream cheese mixture.

title: "coney island" hot dog sauce
directions: Place meat in skillet (medium heat) and cover with water. While this is cooking, mash meat with a potato masher until fine. Add paprika, chili powder, powdered cumin and salt and pepper. Simmer mixture for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
The finer the meat is mashed, the better the flavor when cooking.
Very good.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Hidden Valley mix in bowl.
Divide into 2 balls and roll in bacon bits.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, water, eggs, and softened margarine. Pour 1/2 of the batter into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: veal cordon bleu
directions: Pound meat with a mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put ham and cheese slices on meat to cover only half of surface. Brush meat edges with a little egg white.
Fold together to form "packets."
Press to hold.
Dip meat "packets" in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs.

title: taco cheese dip
directions: Combine in double boiler until melted. If too runny, add more cheese.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press out rolls in round pizza pan.
Sprinkle sausage on top of dough.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: "hot" chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, mayonnaise, almonds, lemon juice and salt.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: a simple zucchini casserole
directions: Place zucchini, garlic powder, basil and pepper in a large pan and parboil for about 5 minutes, then drain well.
Mix together in a separate bowl Monterey Jack, Cheddar and sour cream.
Add to zucchini, then pour into 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Mix together bread crumbs and Parmesan, then sprinkle over top and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: fried apples
directions: Cut apples into 1/2-inch or 3/4-inch thick rings; sprinkle with sugar.
Saute apples until tender on both sides.

title: santee river pilaf
directions: Put in a 12-quart pot the bacon cut in small pieces.
Fry until done.
Add onion and cook brown.
Put water 3/4 full.
Add chicken; boil 15 minutes.
Add sausage, salt and pepper; boil 30 minutes.
Add rice; cook until done.
Stir after.
Well feeds 12 to 25 people.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and beat in. Set aside.
Cream margarine, remaining sugar, egg yolks and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy.
Add milk to dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Coat berries with a little flour.
Pour half of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add berries, then rest of batter.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan or Bundt pan. Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar.
Add cream cheese and beat well.
Alternately add flour and eggs, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and remove to wire rack to complete cooling.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch dish. Pour fruit with juice in the butter. Mix all the other ingredients and pour over fruit. Bake about 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, vinegar and corn meal.
Beat until foamy.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until silver knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 40 minutes).

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Combine the following: raisins, Minute rice and 2 cups boiling water.
Cover and let it set a few minutes.

title: snap casserole
directions: Place ingredients in layers.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dainty dessert *
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and 3/4 cup water.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup water and add to sugar syrup and cool.
Beat egg whites to hold peaks, add cool syrup slowly and beat 20 minutes with electric mixer.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts.
Crush wafers; pour half to line bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour in filling and cover with remaining crushed wafers.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Dessert can also be served in parfait glasses.

title: jiffy chicken or turkey pie
directions: Saute onion in butter; blend in flour and stir well until frothy.
Add soup; heat until thickened.
Add chicken and seasonings.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into greased shallow 3-quart casserole.
Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: beef noodle dinner
directions: Cook beef, salt, bouillon cubes and water in saucepan covered until beef is tender.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Add to beef along with the mushrooms if desired.
Heat until bubbling. Serves 3 to 4.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cinnamon sticks and lemon, in saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, simmer, uncovered 15 minutes.
Remove spices.
Garnish with lemon wedges and cinnamon sticks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute
onions
and
celery
in	margarine.
Combine all ingredients
in
large casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes in microwave on High or bake for 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: two-color pudding
directions: Bring milk to boiling in a double boiler over hot water.
Add pudding, cornstarch, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Continue cooking until thickened.
Divide into two.
Add a different color food coloring to each.
Chill.
Mix graham crackers, margarine and the 1/4 cup sugar.
After the puddings are cool, put graham cracker mixture on top of one color.
(May save some for garnish.)
Put banana slices on top of graham cracker mixture.
Put other color of pudding on top.
Just before serving, slice more bananas on the top and sprinkle with reserved graham cracker mixture.

title: whip cream frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk in saucepan.
Cool until thick.
Cream shortening and butter in mixer.
Add sugar and beat for 4 minutes. Add flour paste and beat 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and blend.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Put a third in bottom of flat casserole dish. Over beans, put a third or mushroom soup, water chestnuts, chopped onions and cheese.
Repeat for second and third layer.
Bake 20 minutes in moderate oven (325°).
Remove from oven and cover with the can of French fried onions.
Return to oven for five minutes. Serves 6.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Wear gloves.
Grind up peppers.
Combine with vinegar, mustard and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Mix flour and water until smooth and then add to pepper mixture.
Stir until thick.
Put in hot jars, boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Yields 12 (12 ounce) jars.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup very warm water and the yeast.
Add 2 cups very warm water, sugar, salt and flour.
Place in a gallon jar and let it sit at room temperature for 3 days.
Stir once a day. Cover loosely, then use or refrigerate.
As you use recipe, take 1 cup and add back 1/2 cup flour plus 1 cup lukewarm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let set out a day, then refrigerate.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Pound chicken breasts on cutting board until 1/4 inch thick. Combine eggs and salt and pepper.
Dip breasts into egg mixture, then into bread crumbs to coat.
Brown both sides of chicken in the oil.
In a saucepan, stir together tomato sauce, basil and garlic powder, and heat to boiling; simmer 10 minutes, or until thickened.
Stir in butter.
Put chicken in a 9 x 13 inch pan and cover with the sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; uncover.
Place mozzarella triangles over chicken and bake 10 minutes longer, or until cheese melts. Serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck, drain off grease.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle taco seasoning on meat.
Moisten with picante sauce.
Drain beans and add to meat.
Add green pepper and onion to meat, if desired (my kids like it without).

title: chicken in a biscuit
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk, beat until smooth.
Add chicken, onion, salt and pepper; stir well.
Separate crescent roll dough into 2 rectangles, firmly pressing perforations to seal, cut each rectangle into 4 rectangles.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of chicken mixture on each rectangle.
Fold sides and ends of dough toward center, moisten edges with water and pinch to seal. Shape into biscuits.
Place seam side down on cookie sheet.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese, bacon, potato casserole
directions: Place stick of butter in bottom of baking pan; arrange potatoes and onions in alternate layers.
Top with bacon strips. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil. Spread cheese on top.
Put back in oven.
Let cheese melt.

title: meat sauce
directions: Brown ground sirloin, onion and garlic in pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve over pasta.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.
You can double and freeze this recipe so you will have it on hand.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Cook in loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder and pepper and place in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Dot with butter and pour wine over top. Broil 7-inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown, turning once. Remove from oven; cool slightly. Drain drippings and reserve. Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Set aside.

title: corn chip cheese dip
directions: Cook Mexican Velveeta cheese and evaporated milk together. Add cooked sausage.
Keep warm.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: In skillet, brown sausage and chicken, stirring often.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, plus 1 cup of water. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Season to taste with pepper.
Serves 4.

title: double chocolate puff bars
directions: Butter a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Pour corn syrup
into a large microwavable bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on High about 1 minute and 30 seconds or until boiling.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in the cereal until it is evenly coated.
Rub a little butter on the back of a spoon.
Use the spoon to press the cereal mixture into the pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes about 20 bars.

title: jiffy cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan that has been greased.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together with a spoon or fork.
(Never mind the lumps, they're supposed to be there.)
Spoon into a greased loaf pan. Spread dough over bottom of pan and into corners.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Brush top with butter.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes or longer. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chili con carne(fast and easy)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off excess fat.
In large pot (great in crock-pot) combine meat with onion, salt, chili powder, bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce and kidney beans.
Cover and cook on low on top of stove (or cook on high in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours also) for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: western skillet rice
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat stirring frequently.
Stir in Lipton Onion soup mix, water, rice, tomatoes and peas.
Simmer covered for 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Top with cheese.

title: chili
directions: Saute vegetables in a small amount of vegetable oil in a large saucepan.
Add ground chuck and brown; drain.
Add tomato puree, paste and stewed tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder. Mix together, then add the juice.
Simmer over low heat for at least an hour, but it can simmer for a few hours, depending on the thickness wanted.
About 1/2 hour before serving, add beans and let heat through.
Taste and adjust seasonings as needed.
This chili is even better the next day.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Enough	buttermilk to make soft dough.	Roll out lightly.
Cut biscuits and prick with fork.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Add flour to the grated potatoes until the mixture is coarse, but stable.
Add salt and mix.

title: stuffed pita
directions: Cut pita bread in half. Seal in aluminum foil and heat in oven at 350° for 5 minutes. Remove from oven and keep warm.
Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until vegetables are tender. Stir in ham and cook until thoroughly heated. Add eggs and cook, stirring frequently, until eggs are set.
Stir in shredded Swiss cheese; remove from heat.
Place 2 tomato slices inside each pita half. Fill with 1/4 cup egg mixture.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt and milk in large heavy kettle. Boil over low heat until a firm ball forms (242° to 248°) when tested in water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Let set for 10 minutes (or until it reaches 110°). Beat until shine leaves candy.
Add condensed milk only if it hardens too much before removing from pan.
Place on large buttered cookie sheet.
Cut with buttered knife before it becomes firm.
Yields 60 pieces.

title: maraschino cherry-nut bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Then add flour, baking powder, cherries, liquid and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour.
NOTE:
Cherries can be left whole, cut in half, chopped into smaller pieces, or to your preference.

title: skillet supper
directions: Roll balls in flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Brown in shortening.
Add potatoes, carrots and peas.
Place all vegetables in skillet with meatballs.
Add 3 cups water.
Simmer for about 1 hour or until vegetables and meat are done.

title: spinach vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill and serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: oysters masca
directions: Saute
onion and garlic in butter; add seasonings.
Add oysters;
add liquid and seasoned bread crumbs.
Put in casserole. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In large Dutch oven, stir flour and oil until smooth.
Cook over medium-high heat, 5 minutes, stir constantly.
Lower to medium, stir constantly, 10 minutes, until red-brown roux forms. Add onions, green pepper and garlic.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in chicken broth, okra, salt, red and black pepper and bay leaves.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and cover 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and crab meat. Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Season to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: twisted zucchini loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine first 4 ingredients. Squeeze water from zucchini; stir zucchini into bowl with remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased 9-inch loaf pan 1 hour. Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: black-eyed pea jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, pepper and garlic in bacon grease.
After 10 minutes, add black-eyed peas and simmer 1/2 hour.
Mix rice, peas and meat together.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in sheet pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: louie's one step lasagne
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups water, spaghetti sauce and browned beef. Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with 1 1/2 cups of sauce.
Arrange lasagne noodles (uncooked) in a layer on top of sauce.
Spread 1/2 of Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese over noodles and sauce.
Repeat covering noodles with sauce.
Sprinkle 2 more tablespoons of Parmesan cheese over top and cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand, covered, 10 minutes before serving.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs or potato chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in pot.
Simmer approximately 1 hour.
Add cut up green peppers and sliced onions.
Simmer an additional 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together and add remaining ingredients.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend 2 cups flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside. Combine sugar, margarine and oil in bowl; beat thoroughly, after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with pineapple (beginning and ending with flour).
Add 1/4 cup flour with nuts and carrots.
Fold this in last.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Test to check if done.
Cool cake and frost with frosting.

title: kit-kat bars
directions: Mix all together.
In large saucepan, boil 5 minutes.
Take 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make a single layer to cover bottom of pan with Waverly crackers.

Pour half of cooked mixture over cracker layer, then place 2nd layer of Waverly crackers over top of mixture. Pour rest of cooked mixture over this 2nd layer of crackers, then place 3rd layer of crackers over last cooked layer.
Press down lightly.
Melt together in microwave 1/2 cup chocolate chips, 1/2 cup butterscotch chips and 2/3 cup peanut butter.
Blend together well.
Frost last layer of crackers (or top of bars) with frosting.
Let cool a little and cut.
No bake and very good.

title: custard sauce
directions: Heat milk in top of double boiler, over direct heat, until bubbles form around edge of pan.
In small bowl, lightly beat egg yolks with sugar and salt.
Gradually add hot milk, beating constantly.
Return to double boiler.
Cook over hot, not boiling, water until thin coating forms on metal spoon, 8 to 10 minutes. Stir in vanilla.
Strain into small bowl.
Refrigerate, covered, until well chilled.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in a frying pan.
Add onion, pepper, and garlic. Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and blend well.
Stir in cooked rice.
Cover pan and cook at low heat until tomato juices are absorbed (about 15 minutes).
Serves 6.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Add lemon juice and egg yolks.
Pour in 2 cups boiling water.
Put on medium-high burner to thicken, stirring constantly.
When thick, remove from heat and add butter.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue made from egg whites and sugar.
Brown in hot oven.

title: seven-flavor precious chicken
directions: Blend 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 1 tablespoon sesame oil with cornstarch.
Stir in chicken strips and let stand 10 minutes. Break vermicelli in half and cook according to package.
Add sesame oil and vinegar; set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in hot wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Remove.
Heat remaining vegetable oil in same pan.
Add carrot and snow peas.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add remaining 3 ingredients and stir-fry 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat; stir in chicken and vinegar mixture.
Pour over hot vermicelli and toss to combine.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: l. a. earthquake cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan.
Put coconut and nuts on bottom. Mix cake according to box directions.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix last 3 ingredients.
Place a tablespoon at a time over all of the cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy cheese pie
directions: Combine ingredients in mixer, except for crust.
Will thicken fast so pour into shell.
Let set in fridge for 1 hour before serving.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon and remove bones.
Cream the cream cheese.
Blend in other ingredients.
When well blended, gently add salmon.
Shape into ball and roll in mixture of nuts and parsley.

title: magic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass).
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, melt butter. Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool before cutting.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Let oleo melt in dish in 350° oven.
Scatter rice in dish. Brown chops and place over rice.
Pour water and then onion soup in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then beat in remainder of ingredients. Put in unbaked pie shell.
Turn on oven to 450°.
Put in pie and turn oven down to 350°.
Bake about 1 hour.
Quick and easy.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Steam cabbage whole until leaves can be pulled off.
Mix meat, rice and diced onions together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Roll meat mixture in cabbage leaves and place in a large oblong baking pan or dish.
Pour the condensed tomato soup over the rolls. Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and continue cooking until slightly browned.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown chops in shortening; drain off excess fat.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Combine all other ingredients. Pour over chops.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes basting occasionally.

title: new potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/2 inch thick.
Arrange in layers in the following order:
potatoes, green onions, bell pepper, butter, salt and pepper.
Place in a covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend all in a blender.
Chill 24 hours.
This recipe makes a lot and is excellent with all fresh vegetables.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Place one boneless chicken breast on a square piece of aluminum foil.
On top, place slices of onion, red bell pepper, yellow bell pepper and sliced water chestnuts.
Pile it on because it will shrink as it cooks.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Sprinkle with teriyaki sauce and seal the aluminum foil.
Place on preheated grill.
Cook on low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with white rice.

title: chocolate cowboy cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa, milk and salt in saucepan.
Boil over medium heat 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Spoon drop onto waxed paper; let cool.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into cornbread crust.
Sprinkle a few cornbread crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, 400°
for 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix bread, vanilla, sugar, milk, nutmeg, cinnamon, margarine, raisins and nuts.
Beat eggs and mix with other mixture.
Spray biscuit pan with Mazola or Pam spray on bottom and all sides. Pour mixture into pan and bake in preheated oven at 350° to 375° until pudding is done.
(Be sure pudding is brown on top.)
Serve hot or cold as desired.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Mix together vegetable oil, Parmesan cheese, salt, garlic powder, paprika and pepper.
Brush on potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes, brushing occasionally with the sauce.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salt water until tender.
Drain. Combine noodles, tuna, mayo, vegetables and salt.
Blend soup and milk.
Heat through.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Add to noodle mixture.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: granny miller's potato soup
directions: Place diced potatoes in a large soup pot. Add water to just below level of potatoes.
Add salt, carrots and onion.
Cook, covered, stirring over medium-low heat until cooked down.
Mash potatoes when soft.
Take off heat and add margarine.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Add sour cream. Add milk to desired consistency.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 day. Reheat and serve.

title: christmas nut bread and date bread
directions: Leave nuts whole.
Cut dates in half.
Slice Brazil nuts lengthwise.
Put nuts in large bowl.
Add dry ingredients, egg yolks and vanilla; mix well.
This will be very stiff.
Stir until nuts and dates are well coated with eggs.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake slowly at 300° for about 1 hour.
Makes 4 small loaves.
Grease pans well or spray with Pam.
Remove from pans immediately as you take them from the oven.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Put
Cool
Whip
(thawed)
in
mixing bowl; add cottage cheese.
Stir to mix well.	Sprinkle jello over mixture.
Stir to mix well.
Fold in oranges and pineapple tidbits.
Store in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.

title: veal or chicken pot pie
directions: Peel potatoes and onions.
Cut celery into desired size and chop parsley.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water and add to gravy.
Combine all ingredients and bake in a covered casserole for 1 hour in a moderate 350° oven.
Remove from oven and cover with pastry or biscuit crust.
Bake in a hot oven at 450° until browned.
Serves 4.

title: party pizza
directions: Combine sausage, garlic salt and oregano in bowl, mixing well. Spread 1 tablespoon mixture on each bread slice.
Top with small amount of cheese.
Place on baking sheet; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until bubbly.
Yields 40 servings.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Fry sausage; crumble and drain.
Beat together soup, egg, mustard and milk.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer croutons first, the cheese second, sausage third and egg mixture fourth.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, then bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered during last 1/2 hour of baking time.
Can prepare ahead of time and freeze.
(Be sure to refrigerate first, then freeze.) Thaw before baking.

title: sunny morning
directions: Combine orange juice and liqueur in container of electric blender.
Add enough ice to bring to 3 1/2-cup level; process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Transfer to a pitcher and stir in champagne.
Garnish, if desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple in water.
Add jello. Stir until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: pizza spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 1/2 tablespoons of butter.
Toss cooked spaghetti with remaining butter and 1 can tomato sauce.
Add half of Swiss cheese, half of pepperoni and half of Mozzarella cheese. Spoon in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Top with remaining can of tomato sauce, Swiss cheese, pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: harvest-time vegetable casserole
directions: Place eggplants in a large saucepan; cover with water and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain and combine with all remaining ingredients, except for 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart flat casserole.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes; top with 1/4 to 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: charlene's garlic dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: pound cake #2
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending each until smooth.
Add flour, one cup at a time, to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Then fold in dry Dream Whip.
Pour in 12-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Allow to cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.
Good luck.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in milk and melted shortening to make a soft dough.
Drop dumplings by spoonfuls into gently boiling broth.
Cover lightly and steam, without lifting cover for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot-nut bread
directions: Beat eggs well, then add sugar and oil and beat until light. Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in with egg mixture and stir until just moistened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake in preheated 350° oven about 1 1/4 hours.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes, then remove pan and cool.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add cooking oil slowly and beat well. Combine dry ingredients and stir in well.
Add apples, pecans, cherries, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch round 4-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
